  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Promise of the Holy Spirit'
      title: The Promise of the Holy Spirit
      number: 1
      content: '  In the first book, O Theophilus, I have dealt with all that Jesus
        began to do and teach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'until the day when he was taken up, after he had given commands through
        the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He presented himself alive to them after his suffering by many proofs,
        appearing to them during forty days and speaking about the kingdom of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And while staying[[COMMENT(0)]] with them he ordered them not to
        depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father, which,
        he said, <JESUS>\u201Cyou heard from me;</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: The Ascension'
      title: The Ascension
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>for </JESUS><JESUS>John baptized with water, </JESUS><JESUS>but
        you will be baptized </JESUS><JESUS>with</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the
        Holy Spirit not many days from now.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So when they had come together, they asked him, \u201CLord, will
        you at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIt is not for you to know </JESUS><JESUS>times
        or seasons that the Father has fixed by his own authority.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>But you will receive </JESUS><JESUS>power </JESUS><JESUS>when
        the Holy Spirit has come upon you, and </JESUS><JESUS>you will be </JESUS><JESUS>my
        witnesses in Jerusalem and in all Judea and </JESUS><JESUS>Samaria, and </JESUS><JESUS>to
        the end of the earth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when he had said these things, as they were looking on, he was
        lifted up, and a cloud took him out of their sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And while they were gazing into heaven as he went, behold, two men
        stood by them in white robes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Matthias Chosen to Replace Judas'
      title: Matthias Chosen to Replace Judas
      number: 11
      content: "and said, \u201CMen of Galilee, why do you stand looking into heaven?
        This Jesus, who was taken up from you into heaven, will come in the same
        way as you saw him go into heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which
        is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day\u2019s journey away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when they had entered, they went up to the upper room, where
        they were staying, Peter and John and James and Andrew, Philip and Thomas,
        Bartholomew and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot and
        Judas the son of James. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'All these with one accord were devoting themselves to prayer, together
        with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus, and his brothers.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: "Or . In New Testament usage, depending on the context, the plural
          Greek word (translated \u201Cbrothers\u201D) may refer either to or to
          ; also verse 15"
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days Peter stood up among the brothers (the company of persons
        was in all about 120) and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBrothers, the Scripture had to be fulfilled, which the Holy
        Spirit spoke beforehand by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who became
        a guide to those who arrested Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For he was numbered among us and was allotted his share in this ministry.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(Now this man acquired a field with the reward of his wickedness,
        and falling headlong[[COMMENT(0)]] he burst open in the middle and all his
        bowels gushed out. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it became known to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that
        the field was called in their own language Akeldama, that is, Field of Blood.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor it is written in the Book of Psalms,  \u201C\u2018May his
        camp become desolate,and let there be no one to dwell in it\u2019;and  \u201C\u2018Let
        another take his office.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So one of the men who have accompanied us during all the time that
        the Lord Jesus went in and out among us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "beginning from the baptism of John until the day when he was taken
        up from us\u2014one of these men must become with us a witness to his resurrection.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they put forward two, Joseph called Barsabbas, who was also called
        Justus, and Matthias. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they prayed and said, \u201CYou, Lord, who know the hearts of
        all, show which one of these two you have chosen "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "to take the place in this ministry and apostleship from which Judas
        turned aside to go to his own place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And they cast lots for them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he
        was numbered with the eleven apostles.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming of the Holy Spirit'
      title: The Coming of the Holy Spirit
      number: 1
      content: '  When the day of Pentecost arrived, they were all together in one
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And suddenly there came from heaven a sound like a mighty rushing
        wind, and it filled the entire house where they were sitting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And divided tongues as of fire appeared to them and rested[[COMMENT(0)]]
        on each one of them. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak
        in other tongues as the Spirit gave them utterance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men from every
        nation under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And at this sound the multitude came together, and they were bewildered,
        because each one was hearing them speak in his own language. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they were amazed and astonished, saying, \u201CAre not all these
        who are speaking Galileans? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And how is it that we hear, each of us in his own native language? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Parthians and Medes and Elamites and residents of Mesopotamia, Judea
        and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya belonging to
        Cyrene, and visitors from Rome, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "both Jews and proselytes, Cretans and Arabians\u2014we hear them
        telling in our own tongues the mighty works of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And all were amazed and perplexed, saying to one another, \u201CWhat
        does this mean?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Peter\u2019s Sermon at Pentecost"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Sermon at Pentecost"
      number: 13
      content: "But others mocking said, \u201CThey are filled with new wine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter, standing with the eleven, lifted up his voice and addressed
        them: \u201CMen of Judea and all who dwell in Jerusalem, let this be known
        to you, and give ear to my words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For these people are not drunk, as you suppose, since it is only
        the third hour of the day.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: 'That is, 9 '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But this is what was uttered through the prophet Joel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201C\u2018And in the last days it shall be, God declares,  that
        I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh,and your sons and your daughters shall
        prophesy,and your young men shall see visions,and your old men shall dream
        dreams;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'even on my male servants and female servantsin those days I will
        pour out my Spirit, and they shall prophesy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will show wonders in the heavens aboveand signs on the earth
        below,blood, and fire, and vapor of smoke;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  the sun shall be turned to darknessand the moon to blood,before
        the day of the Lord comes, the great and magnificent day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And it shall come to pass that everyone who calls upon the name of
        the Lord shall be saved.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMen of Israel, hear these words: Jesus of Nazareth, a man attested
        to you by God with mighty works and wonders and signs that God did through
        him in your midst, as you yourselves know\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'this Jesus,[[COMMENT(0)]]  delivered up according to the definite
        plan and foreknowledge of God, you crucified and killed by the hands of lawless
        men. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'God raised him up, loosing the pangs of death, because it was not
        possible for him to be held by it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David says concerning him,  \u201C\u2018I saw the Lord always
        before me,for he is at my right hand that I may not be shaken;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'therefore my heart was glad, and my tongue rejoiced;my flesh also
        will dwell in hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For you will not abandon my soul to Hades,  or let your Holy One
        see corruption.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You have made known to me the paths of life;you will make me full
        of gladness with your presence.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CBrothers, I may say to you with confidence about the patriarch
        David that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Being therefore a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an
        oath to him that he would set one of his descendants on his throne, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'he foresaw and spoke about the resurrection of the Christ, that he
        was not abandoned to Hades, nor did his flesh see corruption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'This Jesus God raised up, and of that we all are witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Being therefore exalted at the right hand of God, and having received
        from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured out this that
        you yourselves are seeing and hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For David did not ascend into the heavens, but he himself says, 
        \u201C\u2018The Lord said to my Lord,\u201CSit at my right hand,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "until I make your enemies your footstool.\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Let all the house of Israel therefore know for certain that God has
        made him both Lord and Christ, this Jesus whom you crucified.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now when they heard this they were cut to the heart, and said to
        Peter and the rest of the apostles, \u201CBrothers, what shall we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Peter said to them, \u201CRepent and be baptized every one of
        you in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins, and you
        will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For the promise is for you and for your children and for all who
        are far off, everyone whom the Lord our God calls to himself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And with many other words he bore witness and continued to exhort
        them, saying, \u201CSave yourselves from this crooked generation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: The Fellowship of the Believers'
      title: The Fellowship of the Believers
      number: 41
      content: 'So those who received his word were baptized, and there were added
        that day about three thousand souls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And they devoted themselves to the apostles\u2019 teaching and the
        fellowship, to the breaking of bread and the prayers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And awe[[COMMENT(0)]] came upon every soul, and many wonders and
        signs were being done through the apostles. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:43 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And all who believed were together and had all things in common. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And they were selling their possessions and belongings and distributing
        the proceeds to all, as any had need. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And day by day, attending the temple together and breaking bread
        in their homes, they received their food with glad and generous hearts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: praising God and having favor with all the people. And the Lord added
        to their number day by day those who were being saved.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lame Beggar Healed'
      title: The Lame Beggar Healed
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Peter and John were going up to the temple at the hour of prayer,
        the ninth hour.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: 'That is, 3 '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And a man lame from birth was being carried, whom they laid daily
        at the gate of the temple that is called the Beautiful Gate to ask alms of
        those entering the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple, he asked to receive
        alms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Peter directed his gaze at him, as did John, and said, \u201CLook
        at us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he fixed his attention on them, expecting to receive something
        from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CI have no silver and gold, but what I do have
        I give to you. In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and walk!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he took him by the right hand and raised him up, and immediately
        his feet and ankles were made strong. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And leaping up, he stood and began to walk, and entered the temple
        with them, walking and leaping and praising God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And all the people saw him walking and praising God, '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Peter Speaks in Solomon\u2019s Portico"
      title: "Peter Speaks in Solomon\u2019s Portico"
      number: 10
      content: 'and recognized him as the one who sat at the Beautiful Gate of the
        temple, asking for alms. And they were filled with wonder and amazement at
        what had happened to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  While he clung to Peter and John, all the people, utterly astounded,
        ran together to them in the portico called Solomon\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And when Peter saw it he addressed the people: \u201CMen of Israel,
        why do you wonder at this, or why do you stare at us, as though by our own
        power or piety we have made him walk? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, the God
        of our fathers, glorified his servant[[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus, whom you delivered
        over and denied in the presence of Pilate, when he had decided to release
        him. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: Or ; also verse 26
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But you denied the Holy and Righteous One, and asked for a murderer
        to be granted to you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and you killed the Author of life, whom God raised from the dead.
        To this we are witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And his name\u2014by faith in his name\u2014has made this man strong
        whom you see and know, and the faith that is through Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]]
        has given the man this perfect health in the presence of you all.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd now, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance, as did
        also your rulers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But what God foretold by the mouth of all the prophets, that his
        Christ would suffer, he thus fulfilled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Repent therefore, and turn back, that your sins may be blotted out, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord,
        and that he may send the Christ appointed for you, Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'whom heaven must receive until the time for restoring all the things
        about which God spoke by the mouth of his holy prophets long ago. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Moses said, \u2018The Lord God will raise up for you a prophet like
        me from your brothers. You shall listen to him in whatever he tells you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it shall be that every soul who does not listen to that prophet
        shall be destroyed from the people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all the prophets who have spoken, from Samuel and those who came
        after him, also proclaimed these days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You are the sons of the prophets and of the covenant that God made
        with your fathers, saying to Abraham, \u2018And in your offspring shall all
        the families of the earth be blessed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "God, having raised up his servant, sent him to you first, to bless
        you by turning every one of you from your wickedness.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter and John Before the Council'
      title: Peter and John Before the Council
      number: 1
      content: '  And as they were speaking to the people, the priests and the captain
        of the temple and the Sadducees came upon them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'greatly annoyed because they were teaching the people and proclaiming
        in Jesus the resurrection from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they arrested them and put them in custody until the next day,
        for it was already evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But many of those who had heard the word believed, and the number
        of the men came to about five thousand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the next day their rulers and elders and scribes gathered together
        in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'with Annas the high priest and Caiaphas and John and Alexander, and
        all who were of the high-priestly family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when they had set them in the midst, they inquired, \u201CBy
        what power or by what name did you do this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, \u201CRulers
        of the people and elders, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'if we are being examined today concerning a good deed done to a crippled
        man, by what means this man has been healed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "let it be known to all of you and to all the people of Israel that
        by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God raised
        from the dead\u2014by him this man is standing before you well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] is the stone that was rejected by you, the
        builders, which has become the cornerstone.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: 'Greek Greek '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name
        under heaven given among men[[COMMENT(0)]] by which we must be saved.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:12 '
        content: The Greek word refers here to both men and women
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived
        that they were uneducated, common men, they were astonished. And they recognized
        that they had been with Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But seeing the man who was healed standing beside them, they had
        nothing to say in opposition. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when they had commanded them to leave the council, they conferred
        with one another, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "saying, \u201CWhat shall we do with these men? For that a notable
        sign has been performed through them is evident to all the inhabitants of
        Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But in order that it may spread no further among the people, let
        us warn them to speak no more to anyone in this name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So they called them and charged them not to speak or teach at all
        in the name of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Peter and John answered them, \u201CWhether it is right in the
        sight of God to listen to you rather than to God, you must judge, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "for we cannot but speak of what we have seen and heard.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding
        no way to punish them, because of the people, for all were praising God for
        what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Believers Pray for Boldness'
      title: The Believers Pray for Boldness
      number: 22
      content: 'For the man on whom this sign of healing was performed was more than
        forty years old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When they were released, they went to their friends and reported
        what the chief priests and the elders had said to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when they heard it, they lifted their voices together to God
        and said, \u201CSovereign Lord, who made the heaven and the earth and the
        sea and everything in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "who through the mouth of our father David, your servant,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        said by the Holy Spirit,  \u201C\u2018Why did the Gentiles rage,and the peoples
        plot in vain?  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:25 '
        content: Or ; also verses 27, 30
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The kings of the earth set themselves,and the rulers were gathered
        together,against the Lord and against his Anointed\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'for truly in this city there were gathered together against your
        holy servant Jesus, whom you anointed, both Herod and Pontius Pilate, along
        with the Gentiles and the peoples of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'to do whatever your hand and your plan had predestined to take place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And now, Lord, look upon their threats and grant to your servants
        to continue to speak your word with all boldness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "while you stretch out your hand to heal, and signs and wonders are
        performed through the name of your holy servant Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: They Had Everything in Common'
      title: They Had Everything in Common
      number: 31
      content: 'And when they had prayed, the place in which they were gathered together
        was shaken, and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and continued to
        speak the word of God with boldness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the full number of those who believed were of one heart and soul,
        and no one said that any of the things that belonged to him was his own,
        but they had everything in common. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And with great power the apostles were giving their testimony to
        the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and great grace was upon them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'There was not a needy person among them, for as many as were owners
        of lands or houses sold them and brought the proceeds of what was sold '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet, and it was distributed to
        each as any had need. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Thus Joseph, who was also called by the apostles Barnabas (which
        means son of encouragement), a Levite, a native of Cyprus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "sold a field that belonged to him and brought the money and laid
        it at the apostles\u2019 feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ananias and Sapphira'
      title: Ananias and Sapphira
      number: 1
      content: '  But a man named Ananias, with his wife Sapphira, sold a piece of
        property, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and with his wife\u2019s knowledge he kept back for himself some
        of the proceeds and brought only a part of it and laid it at the apostles\u2019
        feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CAnanias, why has Satan filled your heart to
        lie to the Holy Spirit and to keep back for yourself part of the proceeds
        of the land? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "While it remained unsold, did it not remain your own? And after it
        was sold, was it not at your disposal? Why is it that you have contrived
        this deed in your heart? You have not lied to man but to God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Ananias heard these words, he fell down and breathed his last.
        And great fear came upon all who heard of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The young men rose and wrapped him up and carried him out and buried
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After an interval of about three hours his wife came in, not knowing
        what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Peter said to her, \u201CTell me whether you[[COMMENT(0)]] sold
        the land for so much.\u201D And she said, \u201CYes, for so much.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        content: The Greek for is plural here
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Peter said to her, \u201CHow is it that you have agreed together
        to test the Spirit of the Lord? Behold, the feet of those who have buried
        your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Immediately she fell down at his feet and breathed her last. When
        the young men came in they found her dead, and they carried her out and buried
        her beside her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Many Signs and Wonders Done'
      title: Many Signs and Wonders Done
      number: 11
      content: 'And great fear came upon the whole church and upon all who heard
        of these things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now many signs and wonders were regularly done among the people by
        the hands of the apostles. And they were all together in Solomon\u2019s Portico. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'None of the rest dared join them, but the people held them in high
        esteem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And more than ever believers were added to the Lord, multitudes of
        both men and women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so that they even carried out the sick into the streets and laid
        them on cots and mats, that as Peter came by at least his shadow might fall
        on some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Apostles Arrested and Freed'
      title: The Apostles Arrested and Freed
      number: 16
      content: 'The people also gathered from the towns around Jerusalem, bringing
        the sick and those afflicted with unclean spirits, and they were all healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the high priest rose up, and all who were with him (that is,
        the party of the Sadducees), and filled with jealousy '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'they arrested the apostles and put them in the public prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But during the night an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors
        and brought them out, and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGo and stand in the temple and speak to the people all the
        words of this Life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when they heard this, they entered the temple at daybreak and
        began to teach.Now when the high priest came, and those who were with him,
        they called together the council, all the senate of the people of Israel,
        and sent to the prison to have them brought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But when the officers came, they did not find them in the prison,
        so they returned and reported, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWe found the prison securely locked and the guards standing
        at the doors, but when we opened them we found no one inside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now when the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these
        words, they were greatly perplexed about them, wondering what this would
        come to. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And someone came and told them, \u201CLook! The men whom you put
        in prison are standing in the temple and teaching the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the captain with the officers went and brought them, but not
        by force, for they were afraid of being stoned by the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when they had brought them, they set them before the council.
        And the high priest questioned them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "saying, \u201CWe strictly charged you not to teach in this name,
        yet here you have filled Jerusalem with your teaching, and you intend to
        bring this man\u2019s blood upon us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But Peter and the apostles answered, \u201CWe must obey God rather
        than men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The God of our fathers raised Jesus, whom you killed by hanging him
        on a tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'God exalted him at his right hand as Leader and Savior, to give repentance
        to Israel and forgiveness of sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And we are witnesses to these things, and so is the Holy Spirit,
        whom God has given to those who obey him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When they heard this, they were enraged and wanted to kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But a Pharisee in the council named Gamaliel, a teacher of the law
        held in honor by all the people, stood up and gave orders to put the men
        outside for a little while. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CMen of Israel, take care what you are
        about to do with these men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For before these days Theudas rose up, claiming to be somebody, and
        a number of men, about four hundred, joined him. He was killed, and all who
        followed him were dispersed and came to nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'After him Judas the Galilean rose up in the days of the census and
        drew away some of the people after him. He too perished, and all who followed
        him were scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So in the present case I tell you, keep away from these men and let
        them alone, for if this plan or this undertaking is of man, it will fail; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "but if it is of God, you will not be able to overthrow them. You
        might even be found opposing God!\u201D So they took his advice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'and when they had called in the apostles, they beat them and charged
        them not to speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then they left the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were
        counted worthy to suffer dishonor for the name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And every day, in the temple and from house to house, they did not
        cease teaching and preaching that the Christ is Jesus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seven Chosen to Serve'
      title: Seven Chosen to Serve
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in these days when the disciples were increasing in number,
        a complaint by the Hellenists[[COMMENT(0)]] arose against the Hebrews because
        their widows were being neglected in the daily distribution. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: That is, Greek-speaking Jews
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the twelve summoned the full number of the disciples and said,
        \u201CIt is not right that we should give up preaching the word of God to
        serve tables. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] pick out from among you seven
        men of good repute, full of the Spirit and of wisdom, whom we will appoint
        to this duty. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But we will devote ourselves to prayer and to the ministry of the
        word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And what they said pleased the whole gathering, and they chose Stephen,
        a man full of faith and of the Holy Spirit, and Philip, and Prochorus, and
        Nicanor, and Timon, and Parmenas, and Nicolaus, a proselyte of Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'These they set before the apostles, and they prayed and laid their
        hands on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Stephen Is Seized'
      title: Stephen Is Seized
      number: 7
      content: 'And the word of God continued to increase, and the number of the
        disciples multiplied greatly in Jerusalem, and a great many of the priests
        became obedient to the faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Stephen, full of grace and power, was doing great wonders and
        signs among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then some of those who belonged to the synagogue of the Freedmen
        (as it was called), and of the Cyrenians, and of the Alexandrians, and of
        those from Cilicia and Asia, rose up and disputed with Stephen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But they could not withstand the wisdom and the Spirit with which
        he was speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then they secretly instigated men who said, \u201CWe have heard him
        speak blasphemous words against Moses and God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they stirred up the people and the elders and the scribes, and
        they came upon him and seized him and brought him before the council, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and they set up false witnesses who said, \u201CThis man never ceases
        to speak words against this holy place and the law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "for we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy
        this place and will change the customs that Moses delivered to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And gazing at him, all who sat in the council saw that his face was
        like the face of an angel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Stephen\u2019s Speech"
      title: "Stephen\u2019s Speech"
      number: 1
      content: "  And the high priest said, \u201CAre these things so?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Stephen said:  \u201CBrothers and fathers, hear me. The God of
        glory appeared to our father Abraham when he was in Mesopotamia, before he
        lived in Haran, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said to him, \u2018Go out from your land and from your kindred
        and go into the land that I will show you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he went out from the land of the Chaldeans and lived in Haran.
        And after his father died, God removed him from there into this land in which
        you are now living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Yet he gave him no inheritance in it, not even a foot\u2019s length,
        but promised to give it to him as a possession and to his offspring after
        him, though he had no child. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And God spoke to this effect\u2014that his offspring would be sojourners
        in a land belonging to others, who would enslave them and afflict them four
        hundred years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018But I will judge the nation that they serve,\u2019 said God,
        \u2018and after that they shall come out and worship me in this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he gave him the covenant of circumcision. And so Abraham became
        the father of Isaac, and circumcised him on the eighth day, and Isaac became
        the father of Jacob, and Jacob of the twelve patriarchs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd the patriarchs, jealous of Joseph, sold him into Egypt;
        but God was with him "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and rescued him out of all his afflictions and gave him favor and
        wisdom before Pharaoh, king of Egypt, who made him ruler over Egypt and over
        all his household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now there came a famine throughout all Egypt and Canaan, and great
        affliction, and our fathers could find no food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent out our
        fathers on their first visit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And on the second visit Joseph made himself known to his brothers,
        and Joseph\u2019s family became known to Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Joseph sent and summoned Jacob his father and all his kindred,
        seventy-five persons in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Jacob went down into Egypt, and he died, he and our fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and they were carried back to Shechem and laid in the tomb that Abraham
        had bought for a sum of silver from the sons of Hamor in Shechem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut as the time of the promise drew near, which God had granted
        to Abraham, the people increased and multiplied in Egypt "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'until there arose over Egypt another king who did not know Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He dealt shrewdly with our race and forced our fathers to expose
        their infants, so that they would not be kept alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "At this time Moses was born; and he was beautiful in God\u2019s sight.
        And he was brought up for three months in his father\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "and when he was exposed, Pharaoh\u2019s daughter adopted him and
        brought him up as her own son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Moses was instructed in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and
        he was mighty in his words and deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWhen he was forty years old, it came into his heart to visit
        his brothers, the children of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And seeing one of them being wronged, he defended the oppressed man
        and avenged him by striking down the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He supposed that his brothers would understand that God was giving
        them salvation by his hand, but they did not understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And on the following day he appeared to them as they were quarreling
        and tried to reconcile them, saying, \u2018Men, you are brothers. Why do
        you wrong each other?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the man who was wronging his neighbor thrust him aside, saying,
        \u2018Who made you a ruler and a judge over us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do you want to kill me as you killed the Egyptian yesterday?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At this retort Moses fled and became an exile in the land of Midian,
        where he became the father of two sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CNow when forty years had passed, an angel appeared to him in
        the wilderness of Mount Sinai, in a flame of fire in a bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When Moses saw it, he was amazed at the sight, and as he drew near
        to look, there came the voice of the Lord: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u2018I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham and of Isaac
        and of Jacob.\u2019 And Moses trembled and did not dare to look. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u2018Take off the sandals from your feet,
        for the place where you are standing is holy ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "I have surely seen the affliction of my people who are in Egypt,
        and have heard their groaning, and I have come down to deliver them. And
        now come, I will send you to Egypt.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThis Moses, whom they rejected, saying, \u2018Who made you
        a ruler and a judge?\u2019\u2014this man God sent as both ruler and redeemer
        by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'This man led them out, performing wonders and signs in Egypt and
        at the Red Sea and in the wilderness for forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "This is the Moses who said to the Israelites, \u2018God will raise
        up for you a prophet like me from your brothers.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'This is the one who was in the congregation in the wilderness with
        the angel who spoke to him at Mount Sinai, and with our fathers. He received
        living oracles to give to us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Our fathers refused to obey him, but thrust him aside, and in their
        hearts they turned to Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "saying to Aaron, \u2018Make for us gods who will go before us. As
        for this Moses who led us out from the land of Egypt, we do not know what
        has become of him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And they made a calf in those days, and offered a sacrifice to the
        idol and were rejoicing in the works of their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But God turned away and gave them over to worship the host of heaven,
        as it is written in the book of the prophets:  \u201C\u2018Did you bring
        to me slain beasts and sacrifices,  during the forty years in the wilderness,
        O house of Israel?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "You took up the tent of Molochand the star of your god Rephan,the
        images that you made to worship;and I will send you into exile beyond Babylon.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201COur fathers had the tent of witness in the wilderness, just
        as he who spoke to Moses directed him to make it, according to the pattern
        that he had seen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Our fathers in turn brought it in with Joshua when they dispossessed
        the nations that God drove out before our fathers. So it was until the days
        of David, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'who found favor in the sight of God and asked to find a dwelling
        place for the God of Jacob.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:46 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'But it was Solomon who built a house for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Yet the Most High does not dwell in houses made by hands, as the
        prophet says,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Heaven is my throne,  and the earth is my footstool.What
        kind of house will you build for me, says the Lord,or what is the place of
        my rest?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Did not my hand make all these things?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "  \u201CYou stiff-necked people, uncircumcised in heart and ears,
        you always resist the Holy Spirit. As your fathers did, so do you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Which of the prophets did your fathers not persecute? And they killed
        those who announced beforehand the coming of the Righteous One, whom you
        have now betrayed and murdered, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: The Stoning of Stephen'
      title: The Stoning of Stephen
      number: 53
      content: "you who received the law as delivered by angels and did not keep
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Now when they heard these things they were enraged, and they ground
        their teeth at him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'But he, full of the Holy Spirit, gazed into heaven and saw the glory
        of God, and Jesus standing at the right hand of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "And he said, \u201CBehold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son
        of Man standing at the right hand of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'But they cried out with a loud voice and stopped their ears and rushed
        together[[COMMENT(0)]] at him. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:57 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Then they cast him out of the city and stoned him. And the witnesses
        laid down their garments at the feet of a young man named Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "And as they were stoning Stephen, he called out, \u201CLord Jesus,
        receive my spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "And falling to his knees he cried out with a loud voice, \u201CLord,
        do not hold this sin against them.\u201D And when he had said this, he fell
        asleep."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Ravages the Church'
      title: Saul Ravages the Church
      number: 1
      content: '  And Saul approved of his execution.And there arose on that day
        a great persecution against the church in Jerusalem, and they were all scattered
        throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria, except the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Devout men buried Stephen and made great lamentation over him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Philip Proclaims Christ in Samaria'
      title: Philip Proclaims Christ in Samaria
      number: 3
      content: 'But Saul was ravaging the church, and entering house after house,
        he dragged off men and women and committed them to prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now those who were scattered went about preaching the word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Philip went down to the city[[COMMENT(0)]] of Samaria and proclaimed
        to them the Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:5 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the crowds with one accord paid attention to what was being said
        by Philip, when they heard him and saw the signs that he did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For unclean spirits, crying out with a loud voice, came out of many
        who had them, and many who were paralyzed or lame were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Simon the Magician Believes'
      title: Simon the Magician Believes
      number: 8
      content: 'So there was much joy in that city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But there was a man named Simon, who had previously practiced magic
        in the city and amazed the people of Samaria, saying that he himself was
        somebody great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They all paid attention to him, from the least to the greatest, saying,
        \u201CThis man is the power of God that is called Great.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they paid attention to him because for a long time he had amazed
        them with his magic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the
        kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men
        and women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Even Simon himself believed, and after being baptized he continued
        with Philip. And seeing signs and great miracles[[COMMENT(0)]] performed,
        he was amazed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:13 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when the apostles at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received
        the word of God, they sent to them Peter and John, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'who came down and prayed for them that they might receive the Holy
        Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'for he had not yet fallen on any of them, but they had only been
        baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then they laid their hands on them and they received the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now when Simon saw that the Spirit was given through the laying on
        of the apostles\u2019 hands, he offered them money, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "saying, \u201CGive me this power also, so that anyone on whom I lay
        my hands may receive the Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Peter said to him, \u201CMay your silver perish with you, because
        you thought you could obtain the gift of God with money! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have neither part nor lot in this matter, for your heart is not
        right before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Repent, therefore, of this wickedness of yours, and pray to the Lord
        that, if possible, the intent of your heart may be forgiven you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For I see that you are in the gall[[COMMENT(0)]] of bitterness and
        in the bond of iniquity.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '8:23 '
        content: That is, a bitter fluid secreted by the liver; bile
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Simon answered, \u201CPray for me to the Lord, that nothing of
        what you have said may come upon me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Philip and the Ethiopian Eunuch'
      title: Philip and the Ethiopian Eunuch
      number: 25
      content: 'Now when they had testified and spoken the word of the Lord, they
        returned to Jerusalem, preaching the gospel to many villages of the Samaritans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now an angel of the Lord said to Philip, \u201CRise and go toward
        the south[[COMMENT(0)]] to the road that goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza.\u201D
        This is a desert place. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he rose and went. And there was an Ethiopian, a eunuch, a court
        official of Candace, queen of the Ethiopians, who was in charge of all her
        treasure. He had come to Jerusalem to worship '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and was returning, seated in his chariot, and he was reading the
        prophet Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the Spirit said to Philip, \u201CGo over and join this chariot.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Philip ran to him and heard him reading Isaiah the prophet and
        asked, \u201CDo you understand what you are reading?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CHow can I, unless someone guides me?\u201D And
        he invited Philip to come up and sit with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now the passage of the Scripture that he was reading was this:  \u201CLike
        a sheep he was led to the slaughterand like a lamb before its shearer is
        silent,so he opens not his mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "In his humiliation justice was denied him.Who can describe his generation?For
        his life is taken away from the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And the eunuch said to Philip, \u201CAbout whom, I ask you, does
        the prophet say this, about himself or about someone else?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then Philip opened his mouth, and beginning with this Scripture he
        told him the good news about Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And as they were going along the road they came to some water, and
        the eunuch said, \u201CSee, here is water! What prevents me from being baptized?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:36 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add all or most of verse 37: '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And he commanded the chariot to stop, and they both went down into
        the water, Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And when they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord carried
        Philip away, and the eunuch saw him no more, and went on his way rejoicing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: But Philip found himself at Azotus, and as he passed through he preached
        the gospel to all the towns until he came to Caesarea.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Conversion of Saul'
      title: The Conversion of Saul
      number: 1
      content: '  But Saul, still breathing threats and murder against the disciples
        of the Lord, went to the high priest '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and asked him for letters to the synagogues at Damascus, so that
        if he found any belonging to the Way, men or women, he might bring them bound
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now as he went on his way, he approached Damascus, and suddenly a
        light from heaven shone around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And falling to the ground, he heard a voice saying to him, <JESUS>\u201CSaul,
        Saul, why are you persecuting </JESUS><JESUS>me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, \u201CWho are you, Lord?\u201D And he said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        am Jesus, </JESUS><JESUS>whom you are persecuting.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>But </JESUS><JESUS>rise and enter the city, and you will be
        told </JESUS><JESUS>what you are to do.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The men who were traveling with him stood speechless, hearing the
        voice but seeing no one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Saul rose from the ground, and although his eyes were opened, he
        saw nothing. So they led him by the hand and brought him into Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And for three days he was without sight, and neither ate nor drank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now there was a disciple at Damascus named Ananias. The Lord said
        to him in a vision, <JESUS>\u201CAnanias.\u201D</JESUS> And he said, \u201CHere
        I am, Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CRise and go to the street
        called Straight, and at the house of Judas look for a man </JESUS><JESUS>of
        Tarsus named Saul, for behold, he is praying,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>and he has seen in a vision a man named Ananias come in and
        </JESUS><JESUS>lay his hands on him so that he might regain his sight.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Ananias answered, \u201CLord, I have heard from many about this
        man, how much evil he has done to your saints at Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And here he has authority from the chief priests to bind all who
        call on your name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo, for </JESUS><JESUS>he
        is a chosen instrument of mine to carry my name </JESUS><JESUS>before the
        Gentiles and </JESUS><JESUS>kings and the children of Israel.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>For </JESUS><JESUS>I will show him how much </JESUS><JESUS>he
        must suffer </JESUS><JESUS>for the sake of my name.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Ananias departed and entered the house. And laying his hands on
        him he said, \u201CBrother Saul, the Lord Jesus who appeared to you on the
        road by which you came has sent me so that you may regain your sight and
        be filled with the Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And immediately something like scales fell from his eyes, and he
        regained his sight. Then he rose and was baptized; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Saul Proclaims Jesus in Synagogues'
      title: Saul Proclaims Jesus in Synagogues
      number: 19
      content: 'and taking food, he was strengthened.For some days he was with the
        disciples at Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And immediately he proclaimed Jesus in the synagogues, saying, \u201CHe
        is the Son of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And all who heard him were amazed and said, \u201CIs not this the
        man who made havoc in Jerusalem of those who called upon this name? And has
        he not come here for this purpose, to bring them bound before the chief priests?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Saul Escapes from Damascus'
      title: Saul Escapes from Damascus
      number: 22
      content: 'But Saul increased all the more in strength, and confounded the Jews
        who lived in Damascus by proving that Jesus was the Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  When many days had passed, the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]] plotted to kill
        him, '
      comments:
      - number: '9:23 '
        content: The Greek word refers specifically here to Jewish religious leaders,
          and others under their influence, who opposed the Christian faith in that
          time
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'but their plot became known to Saul. They were watching the gates
        day and night in order to kill him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Saul in Jerusalem'
      title: Saul in Jerusalem
      number: 25
      content: 'but his disciples took him by night and let him down through an opening
        in the wall,[[COMMENT(0)]] lowering him in a basket.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:25 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when he had come to Jerusalem, he attempted to join the disciples.
        And they were all afraid of him, for they did not believe that he was a disciple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Barnabas took him and brought him to the apostles and declared
        to them how on the road he had seen the Lord, who spoke to him, and how at
        Damascus he had preached boldly in the name of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So he went in and out among them at Jerusalem, preaching boldly in
        the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he spoke and disputed against the Hellenists.[[COMMENT(0)]] But
        they were seeking to kill him. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:29 '
        content: That is, Greek-speaking Jews
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And when the brothers learned this, they brought him down to Caesarea
        and sent him off to Tarsus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Healing of Aeneas'
      title: The Healing of Aeneas
      number: 31
      content: 'So the church throughout all Judea and Galilee and Samaria had peace
        and was being built up. And walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort
        of the Holy Spirit, it multiplied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now as Peter went here and there among them all, he came down also
        to the saints who lived at Lydda. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'There he found a man named Aeneas, bedridden for eight years, who
        was paralyzed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And Peter said to him, \u201CAeneas, Jesus Christ heals you; rise
        and make your bed.\u201D And immediately he rose. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Dorcas Restored to Life'
      title: Dorcas Restored to Life
      number: 35
      content: 'And all the residents of Lydda and Sharon saw him, and they turned
        to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now there was in Joppa a disciple named Tabitha, which, translated,
        means Dorcas.[[COMMENT(0)]] She was full of good works and acts of charity. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:36 '
        content: 'The Aramaic name and the Greek name both mean '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In those days she became ill and died, and when they had washed her,
        they laid her in an upper room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Since Lydda was near Joppa, the disciples, hearing that Peter was
        there, sent two men to him, urging him, \u201CPlease come to us without delay.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So Peter rose and went with them. And when he arrived, they took
        him to the upper room. All the widows stood beside him weeping and showing
        tunics[[COMMENT(0)]] and other garments that Dorcas made while she was with
        them. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:39 '
        content: Greek , a long garment worn under the cloak next to the skin
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But Peter put them all outside, and knelt down and prayed; and turning
        to the body he said, \u201CTabitha, arise.\u201D And she opened her eyes,
        and when she saw Peter she sat up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And he gave her his hand and raised her up. Then, calling the saints
        and widows, he presented her alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And it became known throughout all Joppa, and many believed in the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And he stayed in Joppa for many days with one Simon, a tanner.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter and Cornelius'
      title: Peter and Cornelius
      number: 1
      content: '  At Caesarea there was a man named Cornelius, a centurion of what
        was known as the Italian Cohort, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a devout man who feared God with all his household, gave alms generously
        to the people, and prayed continually to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "About the ninth hour of the day[[COMMENT(0)]]  he saw clearly in
        a vision an angel of God come in and say to him, \u201CCornelius.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        content: 'That is, 3 '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he stared at him in terror and said, \u201CWhat is it, Lord?\u201D
        And he said to him, \u201CYour prayers and your alms have ascended as a memorial
        before God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now send men to Joppa and bring one Simon who is called Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He is lodging with one Simon, a tanner, whose house is by the sea.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the angel who spoke to him had departed, he called two of his
        servants and a devout soldier from among those who attended him, '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Peter\u2019s Vision"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Vision"
      number: 8
      content: 'and having related everything to them, he sent them to Joppa.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The next day, as they were on their journey and approaching the city,
        Peter went up on the housetop about the sixth hour[[COMMENT(0)]] to pray. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:9 '
        content: That is, noon
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he became hungry and wanted something to eat, but while they
        were preparing it, he fell into a trance '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and saw the heavens opened and something like a great sheet descending,
        being let down by its four corners upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In it were all kinds of animals and reptiles and birds of the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And there came a voice to him: <JESUS>\u201CRise, Peter; kill and
        eat.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CBy no means, Lord; for I have never eaten anything
        that is common or unclean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the voice came to him again a second time, <JESUS>\u201CWhat
        God has made clean, do not call common.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This happened three times, and the thing was taken up at once to
        heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now while Peter was inwardly perplexed as to what the vision that
        he had seen might mean, behold, the men who were sent by Cornelius, having
        made inquiry for Simon\u2019s house, stood at the gate "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and called out to ask whether Simon who was called Peter was lodging
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And while Peter was pondering the vision, the Spirit said to him,
        \u201CBehold, three men are looking for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Rise and go down and accompany them without hesitation,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for I have sent them.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '10:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Peter went down to the men and said, \u201CI am the one you are
        looking for. What is the reason for your coming?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And they said, \u201CCornelius, a centurion, an upright and God-fearing
        man, who is well spoken of by the whole Jewish nation, was directed by a
        holy angel to send for you to come to his house and to hear what you have
        to say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So he invited them in to be his guests.The next day he rose and went
        away with them, and some of the brothers from Joppa accompanied him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And on the following day they entered Caesarea. Cornelius was expecting
        them and had called together his relatives and close friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Peter entered, Cornelius met him and fell down at his feet and
        worshiped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Peter lifted him up, saying, \u201CStand up; I too am a man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as he talked with him, he went in and found many persons gathered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CYou yourselves know how unlawful it is
        for a Jew to associate with or to visit anyone of another nation, but God
        has shown me that I should not call any person common or unclean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So when I was sent for, I came without objection. I ask then why
        you sent for me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Cornelius said, \u201CFour days ago, about this hour, I was praying
        in my house at the ninth hour,[[COMMENT(0)]] and behold, a man stood before
        me in bright clothing "
      comments:
      - number: '10:30 '
        content: 'That is, 3 '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and said, \u2018Cornelius, your prayer has been heard and your alms
        have been remembered before God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Send therefore to Joppa and ask for Simon who is called Peter. He
        is lodging in the house of Simon, a tanner, by the sea.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Gentiles Hear the Good News'
      title: Gentiles Hear the Good News
      number: 33
      content: "So I sent for you at once, and you have been kind enough to come.
        Now therefore we are all here in the presence of God to hear all that you
        have been commanded by the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So Peter opened his mouth and said: \u201CTruly I understand that
        God shows no partiality, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'but in every nation anyone who fears him and does what is right is
        acceptable to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'As for the word that he sent to Israel, preaching good news of peace
        through Jesus Christ (he is Lord of all), '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'you yourselves know what happened throughout all Judea, beginning
        from Galilee after the baptism that John proclaimed: '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'how God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with
        power. He went about doing good and healing all who were oppressed by the
        devil, for God was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And we are witnesses of all that he did both in the country of the
        Jews and in Jerusalem. They put him to death by hanging him on a tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'but God raised him on the third day and made him to appear, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'not to all the people but to us who had been chosen by God as witnesses,
        who ate and drank with him after he rose from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And he commanded us to preach to the people and to testify that he
        is the one appointed by God to be judge of the living and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: The Holy Spirit Falls on the Gentiles'
      title: The Holy Spirit Falls on the Gentiles
      number: 43
      content: "To him all the prophets bear witness that everyone who believes in
        him receives forgiveness of sins through his name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'While Peter was still saying these things, the Holy Spirit fell on
        all who heard the word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And the believers from among the circumcised who had come with Peter
        were amazed, because the gift of the Holy Spirit was poured out even on the
        Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For they were hearing them speaking in tongues and extolling God.
        Then Peter declared, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CCan anyone withhold water for baptizing these people, who have
        received the Holy Spirit just as we have?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ.
        Then they asked him to remain for some days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter Reports to the Church'
      title: Peter Reports to the Church
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the apostles and the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] who were throughout
        Judea heard that the Gentiles also had received the word of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So when Peter went up to Jerusalem, the circumcision party[[COMMENT(0)]]
        criticized him, saying, '
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou went to uncircumcised men and ate with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Peter began and explained it to them in order: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI was in the city of Joppa praying, and in a trance I saw a
        vision, something like a great sheet descending, being let down from heaven
        by its four corners, and it came down to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Looking at it closely, I observed animals and beasts of prey and
        reptiles and birds of the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I heard a voice saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Rise, Peter; kill
        and eat.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But I said, \u2018By no means, Lord; for nothing common or unclean
        has ever entered my mouth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the voice answered a second time from heaven, <JESUS>\u2018What
        God has made clean, do not call common.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This happened three times, and all was drawn up again into heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And behold, at that very moment three men arrived at the house in
        which we were, sent to me from Caesarea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the Spirit told me to go with them, making no distinction. These
        six brothers also accompanied me, and we entered the man\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he told us how he had seen the angel stand in his house and say,
        \u2018Send to Joppa and bring Simon who is called Peter; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "he will declare to you a message by which you will be saved, you
        and all your household.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'As I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell on them just as on us at
        the beginning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I remembered the word of the Lord, how he said, <JESUS>\u2018John
        baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "If then God gave the same gift to them as he gave to us when we believed
        in the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I that I could stand in God\u2019s way?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Church in Antioch'
      title: The Church in Antioch
      number: 18
      content: "When they heard these things they fell silent. And they glorified
        God, saying, \u201CThen to the Gentiles also God has granted repentance that
        leads to life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Now those who were scattered because of the persecution that arose
        over Stephen traveled as far as Phoenicia and Cyprus and Antioch, speaking
        the word to no one except Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But there were some of them, men of Cyprus and Cyrene, who on coming
        to Antioch spoke to the Hellenists[[COMMENT(0)]] also, preaching the Lord
        Jesus. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:20 '
        content: Or (that is, Greek-speaking non-Jews)
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the hand of the Lord was with them, and a great number who believed
        turned to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The report of this came to the ears of the church in Jerusalem, and
        they sent Barnabas to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he came and saw the grace of God, he was glad, and he exhorted
        them all to remain faithful to the Lord with steadfast purpose, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for he was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit and of faith. And
        a great many people were added to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So Barnabas went to Tarsus to look for Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and when he had found him, he brought him to Antioch. For a whole
        year they met with the church and taught a great many people. And in Antioch
        the disciples were first called Christians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now in these days prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And one of them named Agabus stood up and foretold by the Spirit
        that there would be a great famine over all the world (this took place in
        the days of Claudius). '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So the disciples determined, every one according to his ability,
        to send relief to the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] living in Judea. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And they did so, sending it to the elders by the hand of Barnabas
        and Saul.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: James Killed and Peter Imprisoned'
      title: James Killed and Peter Imprisoned
      number: 1
      content: '  About that time Herod the king laid violent hands on some who belonged
        to the church. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He killed James the brother of John with the sword, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and when he saw that it pleased the Jews, he proceeded to arrest
        Peter also. This was during the days of Unleavened Bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when he had seized him, he put him in prison, delivering him
        over to four squads of soldiers to guard him, intending after the Passover
        to bring him out to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Peter Is Rescued'
      title: Peter Is Rescued
      number: 5
      content: 'So Peter was kept in prison, but earnest prayer for him was made
        to God by the church.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now when Herod was about to bring him out, on that very night, Peter
        was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains, and sentries before
        the door were guarding the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And behold, an angel of the Lord stood next to him, and a light shone
        in the cell. He struck Peter on the side and woke him, saying, \u201CGet
        up quickly.\u201D And the chains fell off his hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the angel said to him, \u201CDress yourself and put on your sandals.\u201D
        And he did so. And he said to him, \u201CWrap your cloak around you and follow
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he went out and followed him. He did not know that what was being
        done by the angel was real, but thought he was seeing a vision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they had passed the first and the second guard, they came to
        the iron gate leading into the city. It opened for them of its own accord,
        and they went out and went along one street, and immediately the angel left
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When Peter came to himself, he said, \u201CNow I am sure that the
        Lord has sent his angel and rescued me from the hand of Herod and from all
        that the Jewish people were expecting.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When he realized this, he went to the house of Mary, the mother of
        John whose other name was Mark, where many were gathered together and were
        praying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when he knocked at the door of the gateway, a servant girl named
        Rhoda came to answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Recognizing Peter\u2019s voice, in her joy she did not open the gate
        but ran in and reported that Peter was standing at the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "They said to her, \u201CYou are out of your mind.\u201D But she kept
        insisting that it was so, and they kept saying, \u201CIt is his angel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Peter continued knocking, and when they opened, they saw him
        and were amazed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But motioning to them with his hand to be silent, he described to
        them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, \u201CTell
        these things to James and to the brothers.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] Then he departed
        and went to another place.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now when day came, there was no little disturbance among the soldiers
        over what had become of Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Death of Herod'
      title: The Death of Herod
      number: 19
      content: 'And after Herod searched for him and did not find him, he examined
        the sentries and ordered that they should be put to death. Then he went down
        from Judea to Caesarea and spent time there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Herod was angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon, and they came
        to him with one accord, and having persuaded Blastus, the king\u2019s chamberlain,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        they asked for peace, because their country depended on the king\u2019s country
        for food. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:20 '
        content: That is, trusted personal attendant
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'On an appointed day Herod put on his royal robes, took his seat upon
        the throne, and delivered an oration to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the people were shouting, \u201CThe voice of a god, and not of
        a man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Immediately an angel of the Lord struck him down, because he did
        not give God the glory, and he was eaten by worms and breathed his last.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But the word of God increased and multiplied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  And Barnabas and Saul returned from[[COMMENT(0)]] Jerusalem when
        they had completed their service, bringing with them John, whose other name
        was Mark.'
      comments:
      - number: '12:25 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Barnabas and Saul Sent Off'
      title: Barnabas and Saul Sent Off
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there were in the church at Antioch prophets and teachers,
        Barnabas, Simeon who was called Niger,[[COMMENT(0)]] Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen
        a lifelong friend of Herod the tetrarch, and Saul. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: 'is a Latin word meaning , or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "While they were worshiping the Lord and fasting, the Holy Spirit
        said, \u201CSet apart for me Barnabas and Saul for the work to which I have
        called them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Barnabas and Saul on Cyprus'
      title: Barnabas and Saul on Cyprus
      number: 3
      content: 'Then after fasting and praying they laid their hands on them and
        sent them off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So, being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went down to Seleucia,
        and from there they sailed to Cyprus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When they arrived at Salamis, they proclaimed the word of God in
        the synagogues of the Jews. And they had John to assist them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When they had gone through the whole island as far as Paphos, they
        came upon a certain magician, a Jewish false prophet named Bar-Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He was with the proconsul, Sergius Paulus, a man of intelligence,
        who summoned Barnabas and Saul and sought to hear the word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Elymas the magician (for that is the meaning of his name) opposed
        them, seeking to turn the proconsul away from the faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Saul, who was also called Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit,
        looked intently at him '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said, \u201CYou son of the devil, you enemy of all righteousness,
        full of all deceit and villainy, will you not stop making crooked the straight
        paths of the Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you will be
        blind and unable to see the sun for a time.\u201D Immediately mist and darkness
        fell upon him, and he went about seeking people to lead him by the hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Paul and Barnabas at Antioch in Pisidia'
      title: Paul and Barnabas at Antioch in Pisidia
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the proconsul believed, when he saw what had occurred, for he
        was astonished at the teaching of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now Paul and his companions set sail from Paphos and came to Perga
        in Pamphylia. And John left them and returned to Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but they went on from Perga and came to Antioch in Pisidia. And on
        the Sabbath day they went into the synagogue and sat down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "After the reading from the Law and the Prophets, the rulers of the
        synagogue sent a message to them, saying, \u201CBrothers, if you have any
        word of encouragement for the people, say it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Paul stood up, and motioning with his hand said:\u201CMen of Israel
        and you who fear God, listen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The God of this people Israel chose our fathers and made the people
        great during their stay in the land of Egypt, and with uplifted arm he led
        them out of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And for about forty years he put up with[[COMMENT(0)]] them in the
        wilderness. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: Some manuscripts (compare Deuteronomy 1:31)
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And after destroying seven nations in the land of Canaan, he gave
        them their land as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All this took about 450 years. And after that he gave them judges
        until Samuel the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they asked for a king, and God gave them Saul the son of Kish,
        a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when he had removed him, he raised up David to be their king,
        of whom he testified and said, \u2018I have found in David the son of Jesse
        a man after my heart, who will do all my will.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Of this man\u2019s offspring God has brought to Israel a Savior,
        Jesus, as he promised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Before his coming, John had proclaimed a baptism of repentance to
        all the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And as John was finishing his course, he said, \u2018What do you
        suppose that I am? I am not he. No, but behold, after me one is coming, the
        sandals of whose feet I am not worthy to untie.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBrothers, sons of the family of Abraham, and those among you
        who fear God, to us has been sent the message of this salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For those who live in Jerusalem and their rulers, because they did
        not recognize him nor understand the utterances of the prophets, which are
        read every Sabbath, fulfilled them by condemning him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And though they found in him no guilt worthy of death, they asked
        Pilate to have him executed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when they had carried out all that was written of him, they took
        him down from the tree and laid him in a tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But God raised him from the dead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and for many days he appeared to those who had come up with him from
        Galilee to Jerusalem, who are now his witnesses to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And we bring you the good news that what God promised to the fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "this he has fulfilled to us their children by raising Jesus, as also
        it is written in the second Psalm,  \u201C\u2018You are my Son,today I have
        begotten you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And as for the fact that he raised him from the dead, no more to
        return to corruption, he has spoken in this way,\u201C\u2018I will give you
        the holy and sure blessings of David.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Therefore he says also in another psalm,  \u201C\u2018You will not
        let your Holy One see corruption.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For David, after he had served the purpose of God in his own generation,
        fell asleep and was laid with his fathers and saw corruption, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'but he whom God raised up did not see corruption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Let it be known to you therefore, brothers, that through this man
        forgiveness of sins is proclaimed to you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and by him everyone who believes is freed[[COMMENT(0)]] from everything
        from which you could not be freed by the law of Moses. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:39 '
        content: Greek ; twice in this verse
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Beware, therefore, lest what is said in the Prophets should come
        about:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Look, you scoffers,be astounded and perish;for I am
        doing a work in your days,a work that you will not believe, even if one tells
        it to you.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'As they went out, the people begged that these things might be told
        them the next Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And after the meeting of the synagogue broke up, many Jews and devout
        converts to Judaism followed Paul and Barnabas, who, as they spoke with them,
        urged them to continue in the grace of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The next Sabbath almost the whole city gathered to hear the word
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'But when the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]] saw the crowds, they were filled
        with jealousy and began to contradict what was spoken by Paul, reviling him. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:45 '
        content: Greek probably refers here to Jewish religious leaders, and others
          under their influence, in that time; also verse 50
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Paul and Barnabas spoke out boldly, saying, \u201CIt was necessary
        that the word of God be spoken first to you. Since you thrust it aside and
        judge yourselves unworthy of eternal life, behold, we are turning to the
        Gentiles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "For so the Lord has commanded us, saying,  \u201C\u2018I have made
        you a light for the Gentiles,that you may bring salvation to the ends of
        the earth.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And when the Gentiles heard this, they began rejoicing and glorifying
        the word of the Lord, and as many as were appointed to eternal life believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And the word of the Lord was spreading throughout the whole region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'But the Jews incited the devout women of high standing and the leading
        men of the city, stirred up persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and drove
        them out of their district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'But they shook off the dust from their feet against them and went
        to Iconium. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: And the disciples were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul and Barnabas at Iconium'
      title: Paul and Barnabas at Iconium
      number: 1
      content: '  Now at Iconium they entered together into the Jewish synagogue
        and spoke in such a way that a great number of both Jews and Greeks believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their
        minds against the brothers.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they remained for a long time, speaking boldly for the Lord, who
        bore witness to the word of his grace, granting signs and wonders to be done
        by their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the people of the city were divided; some sided with the Jews
        and some with the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When an attempt was made by both Gentiles and Jews, with their rulers,
        to mistreat them and to stone them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'they learned of it and fled to Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia,
        and to the surrounding country, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Paul and Barnabas at Lystra'
      title: Paul and Barnabas at Lystra
      number: 7
      content: 'and there they continued to preach the gospel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now at Lystra there was a man sitting who could not use his feet.
        He was crippled from birth and had never walked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He listened to Paul speaking. And Paul, looking intently at him and
        seeing that he had faith to be made well,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "said in a loud voice, \u201CStand upright on your feet.\u201D And
        he sprang up and began walking. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when the crowds saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their
        voices, saying in Lycaonian, \u201CThe gods have come down to us in the likeness
        of men!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Barnabas they called Zeus, and Paul, Hermes, because he was the chief
        speaker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the priest of Zeus, whose temple was at the entrance to the city,
        brought oxen and garlands to the gates and wanted to offer sacrifice with
        the crowds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But when the apostles Barnabas and Paul heard of it, they tore their
        garments and rushed out into the crowd, crying out, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMen, why are you doing these things? We also are men, of like
        nature with you, and we bring you good news, that you should turn from these
        vain things to a living God, who made the heaven and the earth and the sea
        and all that is in them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In past generations he allowed all the nations to walk in their own
        ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Yet he did not leave himself without witness, for he did good by
        giving you rains from heaven and fruitful seasons, satisfying your hearts
        with food and gladness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Paul Stoned at Lystra'
      title: Paul Stoned at Lystra
      number: 18
      content: 'Even with these words they scarcely restrained the people from offering
        sacrifice to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  But Jews came from Antioch and Iconium, and having persuaded the
        crowds, they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, supposing that
        he was dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But when the disciples gathered about him, he rose up and entered
        the city, and on the next day he went on with Barnabas to Derbe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When they had preached the gospel to that city and had made many
        disciples, they returned to Lystra and to Iconium and to Antioch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'strengthening the souls of the disciples, encouraging them to continue
        in the faith, and saying that through many tribulations we must enter the
        kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Paul and Barnabas Return to Antioch in Syria'
      title: Paul and Barnabas Return to Antioch in Syria
      number: 23
      content: 'And when they had appointed elders for them in every church, with
        prayer and fasting they committed them to the Lord in whom they had believed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then they passed through Pisidia and came to Pamphylia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And when they had spoken the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and from there they sailed to Antioch, where they had been commended
        to the grace of God for the work that they had fulfilled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when they arrived and gathered the church together, they declared
        all that God had done with them, and how he had opened a door of faith to
        the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And they remained no little time with the disciples.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Jerusalem Council'
      title: The Jerusalem Council
      number: 1
      content: "    But some men came down from Judea and were teaching the brothers,
        \u201CUnless you are circumcised according to the custom of Moses, you cannot
        be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And after Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and debate with
        them, Paul and Barnabas and some of the others were appointed to go up to
        Jerusalem to the apostles and the elders about this question. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So, being sent on their way by the church, they passed through both
        Phoenicia and Samaria, describing in detail the conversion of the Gentiles,
        and brought great joy to all the brothers.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:3 '
        content: Or ; also verse 22
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When they came to Jerusalem, they were welcomed by the church and
        the apostles and the elders, and they declared all that God had done with
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But some believers who belonged to the party of the Pharisees rose
        up and said, \u201CIt is necessary to circumcise them and to order them to
        keep the law of Moses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The apostles and the elders were gathered together to consider
        this matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And after there had been much debate, Peter stood up and said to
        them, \u201CBrothers, you know that in the early days God made a choice among
        you, that by my mouth the Gentiles should hear the word of the gospel and
        believe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God, who knows the heart, bore witness to them, by giving them
        the Holy Spirit just as he did to us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and he made no distinction between us and them, having cleansed their
        hearts by faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now, therefore, why are you putting God to the test by placing a
        yoke on the neck of the disciples that neither our fathers nor we have been
        able to bear? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But we believe that we will be saved through the grace of the Lord
        Jesus, just as they will.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And all the assembly fell silent, and they listened to Barnabas and
        Paul as they related what signs and wonders God had done through them among
        the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "After they finished speaking, James replied, \u201CBrothers, listen
        to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Simeon has related how God first visited the Gentiles, to take from
        them a people for his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And with this the words of the prophets agree, just as it is written,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201C\u2018After this I will return,and I will rebuild the tent
        of David that has fallen;I will rebuild its ruins,and I will restore it,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'that the remnant[[COMMENT(0)]] of mankind may seek the Lord,and all
        the Gentiles who are called by my name,says the Lord, who makes these things '
      comments:
      - number: '15:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "known from of old.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore my judgment is that we should not trouble those of the
        Gentiles who turn to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but should write to them to abstain from the things polluted by idols,
        and from sexual immorality, and from what has been strangled, and from blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: "21: The Council\u2019s Letter to Gentile Believers"
      title: "The Council\u2019s Letter to Gentile Believers"
      number: 21
      content: "For from ancient generations Moses has had in every city those who
        proclaim him, for he is read every Sabbath in the synagogues.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then it seemed good to the apostles and the elders, with the whole
        church, to choose men from among them and send them to Antioch with Paul
        and Barnabas. They sent Judas called Barsabbas, and Silas, leading men among
        the brothers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "with the following letter: \u201CThe brothers, both the apostles
        and the elders, to the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] who are of the Gentiles in
        Antioch and Syria and Cilicia, greetings. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:23 '
        content: Or ; also verses 32, 33, 36
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Since we have heard that some persons have gone out from us and troubled
        you[[COMMENT(0)]] with words, unsettling your minds, although we gave them
        no instructions, '
      comments:
      - number: '15:24 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'it has seemed good to us, having come to one accord, to choose men
        and send them to you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'We have therefore sent Judas and Silas, who themselves will tell
        you the same things by word of mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For it has seemed good to the Holy Spirit and to us to lay on you
        no greater burden than these requirements: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you abstain from what has been sacrificed to idols, and from
        blood, and from what has been strangled, and from sexual immorality. If you
        keep yourselves from these, you will do well. Farewell.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when they were sent off, they went down to Antioch, and having
        gathered the congregation together, they delivered the letter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And when they had read it, they rejoiced because of its encouragement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Judas and Silas, who were themselves prophets, encouraged and
        strengthened the brothers with many words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And after they had spent some time, they were sent off in peace by
        the brothers to those who had sent them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:33 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts insert verse 34: '
    - name: '35: Paul and Barnabas Separate'
      title: Paul and Barnabas Separate
      number: 35
      content: 'But Paul and Barnabas remained in Antioch, teaching and preaching
        the word of the Lord, with many others also.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And after some days Paul said to Barnabas, \u201CLet us return and
        visit the brothers in every city where we proclaimed the word of the Lord,
        and see how they are.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Now Barnabas wanted to take with them John called Mark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But Paul thought best not to take with them one who had withdrawn
        from them in Pamphylia and had not gone with them to the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And there arose a sharp disagreement, so that they separated from
        each other. Barnabas took Mark with him and sailed away to Cyprus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'but Paul chose Silas and departed, having been commended by the brothers
        to the grace of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Timothy Joins Paul and Silas'
      title: Timothy Joins Paul and Silas
      number: 1
      content: '  Paul[[COMMENT(0)]] came also to Derbe and to Lystra. A disciple
        was there, named Timothy, the son of a Jewish woman who was a believer, but
        his father was a Greek. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:1 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was well spoken of by the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] at Lystra and
        Iconium. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:2 '
        content: Or ; also verse 40
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Paul wanted Timothy to accompany him, and he took him and circumcised
        him because of the Jews who were in those places, for they all knew that
        his father was a Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As they went on their way through the cities, they delivered to them
        for observance the decisions that had been reached by the apostles and elders
        who were in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Macedonian Call'
      title: The Macedonian Call
      number: 5
      content: 'So the churches were strengthened in the faith, and they increased
        in numbers daily.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And they went through the region of Phrygia and Galatia, having been
        forbidden by the Holy Spirit to speak the word in Asia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when they had come up to Mysia, they attempted to go into Bithynia,
        but the Spirit of Jesus did not allow them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So, passing by Mysia, they went down to Troas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And a vision appeared to Paul in the night: a man of Macedonia was
        standing there, urging him and saying, \u201CCome over to Macedonia and help
        us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Conversion of Lydia'
      title: The Conversion of Lydia
      number: 10
      content: 'And when Paul[[COMMENT(0)]] had seen the vision, immediately we sought
        to go on into Macedonia, concluding that God had called us to preach the
        gospel to them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:10 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So, setting sail from Troas, we made a direct voyage to Samothrace,
        and the following day to Neapolis, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and from there to Philippi, which is a leading city of the[[COMMENT(0)]]
        district of Macedonia and a Roman colony. We remained in this city some days. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And on the Sabbath day we went outside the gate to the riverside,
        where we supposed there was a place of prayer, and we sat down and spoke
        to the women who had come together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'One who heard us was a woman named Lydia, from the city of Thyatira,
        a seller of purple goods, who was a worshiper of God. The Lord opened her
        heart to pay attention to what was said by Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Paul and Silas in Prison'
      title: Paul and Silas in Prison
      number: 15
      content: "And after she was baptized, and her household as well, she urged
        us, saying, \u201CIf you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come
        to my house and stay.\u201D And she prevailed upon us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As we were going to the place of prayer, we were met by a slave girl
        who had a spirit of divination and brought her owners much gain by fortune-telling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She followed Paul and us, crying out, \u201CThese men are servants
        of the Most High God, who proclaim to you the way of salvation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And this she kept doing for many days. Paul, having become greatly
        annoyed, turned and said to the spirit, \u201CI command you in the name of
        Jesus Christ to come out of her.\u201D And it came out that very hour.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when her owners saw that their hope of gain was gone, they seized
        Paul and Silas and dragged them into the marketplace before the rulers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when they had brought them to the magistrates, they said, \u201CThese
        men are Jews, and they are disturbing our city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They advocate customs that are not lawful for us as Romans to accept
        or practice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The crowd joined in attacking them, and the magistrates tore the
        garments off them and gave orders to beat them with rods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And when they had inflicted many blows upon them, they threw them
        into prison, ordering the jailer to keep them safely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Philippian Jailer Converted'
      title: The Philippian Jailer Converted
      number: 24
      content: 'Having received this order, he put them into the inner prison and
        fastened their feet in the stocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  About midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to
        God, and the prisoners were listening to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations
        of the prison were shaken. And immediately all the doors were opened, and
        everyone\u2019s bonds were unfastened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the jailer woke and saw that the prison doors were open, he
        drew his sword and was about to kill himself, supposing that the prisoners
        had escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But Paul cried with a loud voice, \u201CDo not harm yourself, for
        we are all here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the jailer[[COMMENT(0)]] called for lights and rushed in, and
        trembling with fear he fell down before Paul and Silas. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:29 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he brought them out and said, \u201CSirs, what must I do to
        be saved?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And they said, \u201CBelieve in the Lord Jesus, and you will be saved,
        you and your household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they spoke the word of the Lord to him and to all who were in
        his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he took them the same hour of the night and washed their wounds;
        and he was baptized at once, he and all his family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then he brought them up into his house and set food before them.
        And he rejoiced along with his entire household that he had believed in God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "But when it was day, the magistrates sent the police, saying, \u201CLet
        those men go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And the jailer reported these words to Paul, saying, \u201CThe magistrates
        have sent to let you go. Therefore come out now and go in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Paul said to them, \u201CThey have beaten us publicly, uncondemned,
        men who are Roman citizens, and have thrown us into prison; and do they now
        throw us out secretly? No! Let them come themselves and take us out.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The police reported these words to the magistrates, and they were
        afraid when they heard that they were Roman citizens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So they came and apologized to them. And they took them out and asked
        them to leave the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: So they went out of the prison and visited Lydia. And when they had
        seen the brothers, they encouraged them and departed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul and Silas in Thessalonica'
      title: Paul and Silas in Thessalonica
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they
        came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Paul went in, as was his custom, and on three Sabbath days he
        reasoned with them from the Scriptures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "explaining and proving that it was necessary for the Christ to suffer
        and to rise from the dead, and saying, \u201CThis Jesus, whom I proclaim
        to you, is the Christ.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And some of them were persuaded and joined Paul and Silas, as did
        a great many of the devout Greeks and not a few of the leading women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]]  were jealous, and taking some wicked
        men of the rabble, they formed a mob, set the city in an uproar, and attacked
        the house of Jason, seeking to bring them out to the crowd. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:5 '
        content: Greek probably refers here to Jewish religious leaders, and others
          under their influence, in that time; also verse 13
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when they could not find them, they dragged Jason and some of
        the brothers before the city authorities, shouting, \u201CThese men who have
        turned the world upside down have come here also, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and Jason has received them, and they are all acting against the
        decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the people and the city authorities were disturbed when they
        heard these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Paul and Silas in Berea'
      title: Paul and Silas in Berea
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they had taken money as security from Jason and the rest,
        they let them go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] immediately sent Paul and Silas away
        by night to Berea, and when they arrived they went into the Jewish synagogue. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:10 '
        content: Or ; also verse 14
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now these Jews were more noble than those in Thessalonica; they received
        the word with all eagerness, examining the Scriptures daily to see if these
        things were so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Many of them therefore believed, with not a few Greek women of high
        standing as well as men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But when the Jews from Thessalonica learned that the word of God
        was proclaimed by Paul at Berea also, they came there too, agitating and
        stirring up the crowds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the brothers immediately sent Paul off on his way to the sea,
        but Silas and Timothy remained there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Paul in Athens'
      title: Paul in Athens
      number: 15
      content: 'Those who conducted Paul brought him as far as Athens, and after
        receiving a command for Silas and Timothy to come to him as soon as possible,
        they departed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now while Paul was waiting for them at Athens, his spirit was provoked
        within him as he saw that the city was full of idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews and the devout persons,
        and in the marketplace every day with those who happened to be there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers also conversed with
        him. And some said, \u201CWhat does this babbler wish to say?\u201D Others
        said, \u201CHe seems to be a preacher of foreign divinities\u201D\u2014because
        he was preaching Jesus and the resurrection. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they took him and brought him to the Areopagus, saying, \u201CMay
        we know what this new teaching is that you are presenting? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For you bring some strange things to our ears. We wish to know therefore
        what these things mean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Paul Addresses the Areopagus'
      title: Paul Addresses the Areopagus
      number: 21
      content: 'Now all the Athenians and the foreigners who lived there would spend
        their time in nothing except telling or hearing something new.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Paul, standing in the midst of the Areopagus, said: \u201CMen
        of Athens, I perceive that in every way you are very religious. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For as I passed along and observed the objects of your worship, I
        found also an altar with this inscription: \u2018To the unknown god.\u2019
        What therefore you worship as unknown, this I proclaim to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The God who made the world and everything in it, being Lord of heaven
        and earth, does not live in temples made by man,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:24 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'nor is he served by human hands, as though he needed anything, since
        he himself gives to all mankind life and breath and everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And he made from one man every nation of mankind to live on all the
        face of the earth, having determined allotted periods and the boundaries
        of their dwelling place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'that they should seek God, and perhaps feel their way toward him
        and find him. Yet he is actually not far from each one of us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "for  \u201C\u2018In him we live and move and have our being\u2019;[[COMMENT(0)]]as
        even some of your own poets have said,\u201C\u2018For we are indeed his offspring.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:28 '
        content: "Probably from Epimenides of CreteFrom Aratus\u2019s poem \u201CPhainomena\u201D"
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  Being then God\u2019s offspring, we ought not to think that the
        divine being is like gold or silver or stone, an image formed by the art
        and imagination of man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The times of ignorance God overlooked, but now he commands all people
        everywhere to repent, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "because he has fixed a day on which he will judge the world in righteousness
        by a man whom he has appointed; and of this he has given assurance to all
        by raising him from the dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked.
        But others said, \u201CWe will hear you again about this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Paul went out from their midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: But some men joined him and believed, among whom also were Dionysius
        the Areopagite and a woman named Damaris and others with them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul in Corinth'
      title: Paul in Corinth
      number: 1
      content: '  After this Paul[[COMMENT(0)]] left Athens and went to Corinth. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:1 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he found a Jew named Aquila, a native of Pontus, recently come
        from Italy with his wife Priscilla, because Claudius had commanded all the
        Jews to leave Rome. And he went to see them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and because he was of the same trade he stayed with them and worked,
        for they were tentmakers by trade. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath, and tried to persuade
        Jews and Greeks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  When Silas and Timothy arrived from Macedonia, Paul was occupied
        with the word, testifying to the Jews that the Christ was Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And when they opposed and reviled him, he shook out his garments
        and said to them, \u201CYour blood be on your own heads! I am innocent. From
        now on I will go to the Gentiles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he left there and went to the house of a man named Titius Justus,
        a worshiper of God. His house was next door to the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Crispus, the ruler of the synagogue, believed in the Lord, together
        with his entire household. And many of the Corinthians hearing Paul believed
        and were baptized. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to Paul one night in a vision, <JESUS>\u201CDo
        not be afraid, but go on speaking and do not be silent,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>for I am with you, and </JESUS><JESUS>no one will attack you
        to harm you, for </JESUS><JESUS>I have many in this city who are my people.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he stayed a year and six months, teaching the word of God among
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]] made
        a united attack on Paul and brought him before the tribunal, '
      comments:
      - number: '18:12 '
        content: Greek probably refers here to Jewish religious leaders, and others
          under their influence, in that time; also verses 14 (twice), 28
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "saying, \u201CThis man is persuading people to worship God contrary
        to the law.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews,
        \u201CIf it were a matter of wrongdoing or vicious crime, O Jews, I would
        have reason to accept your complaint. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But since it is a matter of questions about words and names and your
        own law, see to it yourselves. I refuse to be a judge of these things.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he drove them from the tribunal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Paul Returns to Antioch'
      title: Paul Returns to Antioch
      number: 17
      content: 'And they all seized Sosthenes, the ruler of the synagogue, and beat
        him in front of the tribunal. But Gallio paid no attention to any of this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After this, Paul stayed many days longer and then took leave of the
        brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] and set sail for Syria, and with him Priscilla and
        Aquila. At Cenchreae he had cut his hair, for he was under a vow. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:18 '
        content: Or ; also verse 27
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they came to Ephesus, and he left them there, but he himself
        went into the synagogue and reasoned with the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they asked him to stay for a longer period, he declined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But on taking leave of them he said, \u201CI will return to you if
        God wills,\u201D and he set sail from Ephesus.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When he had landed at Caesarea, he went up and greeted the church,
        and then went down to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Apollos Speaks Boldly in Ephesus'
      title: Apollos Speaks Boldly in Ephesus
      number: 23
      content: 'After spending some time there, he departed and went from one place
        to the next through the region of Galatia and Phrygia, strengthening all
        the disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now a Jew named Apollos, a native of Alexandria, came to Ephesus.
        He was an eloquent man, competent in the Scriptures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He had been instructed in the way of the Lord. And being fervent
        in spirit,[[COMMENT(0)]] he spoke and taught accurately the things concerning
        Jesus, though he knew only the baptism of John. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:25 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He began to speak boldly in the synagogue, but when Priscilla and
        Aquila heard him, they took him aside and explained to him the way of God
        more accurately. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when he wished to cross to Achaia, the brothers encouraged him
        and wrote to the disciples to welcome him. When he arrived, he greatly helped
        those who through grace had believed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: for he powerfully refuted the Jews in public, showing by the Scriptures
        that the Christ was Jesus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul in Ephesus'
      title: Paul in Ephesus
      number: 1
      content: '  And it happened that while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul passed
        through the inland[[COMMENT(0)]] country and came to Ephesus. There he found
        some disciples. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:1 '
        content: Greek (that is, highland)
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CDid you receive the Holy Spirit when you
        believed?\u201D And they said, \u201CNo, we have not even heard that there
        is a Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said, \u201CInto what then were you baptized?\u201D They said,
        \u201CInto John\u2019s baptism.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Paul said, \u201CJohn baptized with the baptism of repentance,
        telling the people to believe in the one who was to come after him, that
        is, Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On hearing this, they were baptized in[[COMMENT(0)]] the name of
        the Lord Jesus. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Paul had laid his hands on them, the Holy Spirit came on
        them, and they began speaking in tongues and prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There were about twelve men in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he entered the synagogue and for three months spoke boldly, reasoning
        and persuading them about the kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But when some became stubborn and continued in unbelief, speaking
        evil of the Way before the congregation, he withdrew from them and took the
        disciples with him, reasoning daily in the hall of Tyrannus.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:9 '
        content: Some manuscripts add (that is, from 11  to 4 )
    - name: '10: The Sons of Sceva'
      title: The Sons of Sceva
      number: 10
      content: 'This continued for two years, so that all the residents of Asia heard
        the word of the Lord, both Jews and Greeks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And God was doing extraordinary miracles by the hands of Paul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that even handkerchiefs or aprons that had touched his skin were
        carried away to the sick, and their diseases left them and the evil spirits
        came out of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then some of the itinerant Jewish exorcists undertook to invoke the
        name of the Lord Jesus over those who had evil spirits, saying, \u201CI adjure
        you by the Jesus whom Paul proclaims.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Seven sons of a Jewish high priest named Sceva were doing this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the evil spirit answered them, \u201CJesus I know, and Paul I
        recognize, but who are you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the man in whom was the evil spirit leaped on them, mastered
        all[[COMMENT(0)]] of them and overpowered them, so that they fled out of
        that house naked and wounded. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And this became known to all the residents of Ephesus, both Jews
        and Greeks. And fear fell upon them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was
        extolled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also many of those who were now believers came, confessing and divulging
        their practices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And a number of those who had practiced magic arts brought their
        books together and burned them in the sight of all. And they counted the
        value of them and found it came to fifty thousand pieces of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: A Riot at Ephesus'
      title: A Riot at Ephesus
      number: 20
      content: 'So the word of the Lord continued to increase and prevail mightily.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now after these events Paul resolved in the Spirit to pass through
        Macedonia and Achaia and go to Jerusalem, saying, \u201CAfter I have been
        there, I must also see Rome.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And having sent into Macedonia two of his helpers, Timothy and Erastus,
        he himself stayed in Asia for a while.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'About that time there arose no little disturbance concerning the
        Way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For a man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines
        of Artemis, brought no little business to the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "These he gathered together, with the workmen in similar trades, and
        said, \u201CMen, you know that from this business we have our wealth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And you see and hear that not only in Ephesus but in almost all of
        Asia this Paul has persuaded and turned away a great many people, saying
        that gods made with hands are not gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And there is danger not only that this trade of ours may come into
        disrepute but also that the temple of the great goddess Artemis may be counted
        as nothing, and that she may even be deposed from her magnificence, she whom
        all Asia and the world worship.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When they heard this they were enraged and were crying out, \u201CGreat
        is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the city was filled with the confusion, and they rushed together
        into the theater, dragging with them Gaius and Aristarchus, Macedonians who
        were Paul\u2019s companions in travel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But when Paul wished to go in among the crowd, the disciples would
        not let him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And even some of the Asiarchs,[[COMMENT(0)]] who were friends of
        his, sent to him and were urging him not to venture into the theater. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:31 '
        content: That is, high-ranking officers of the province of Asia
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now some cried out one thing, some another, for the assembly was
        in confusion, and most of them did not know why they had come together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Some of the crowd prompted Alexander, whom the Jews had put forward.
        And Alexander, motioning with his hand, wanted to make a defense to the crowd. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But when they recognized that he was a Jew, for about two hours they
        all cried out with one voice, \u201CGreat is Artemis of the Ephesians!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And when the town clerk had quieted the crowd, he said, \u201CMen
        of Ephesus, who is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians
        is temple keeper of the great Artemis, and of the sacred stone that fell
        from the sky?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:35 '
        content: The meaning of the Greek is uncertain
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Seeing then that these things cannot be denied, you ought to be quiet
        and do nothing rash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For you have brought these men here who are neither sacrilegious
        nor blasphemers of our goddess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'If therefore Demetrius and the craftsmen with him have a complaint
        against anyone, the courts are open, and there are proconsuls. Let them bring
        charges against one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But if you seek anything further,[[COMMENT(0)]] it shall be settled
        in the regular assembly. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:39 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For we really are in danger of being charged with rioting today,
        since there is no cause that we can give to justify this commotion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And when he had said these things, he dismissed the assembly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul in Macedonia and Greece'
      title: Paul in Macedonia and Greece
      number: 1
      content: '  After the uproar ceased, Paul sent for the disciples, and after
        encouraging them, he said farewell and departed for Macedonia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When he had gone through those regions and had given them much encouragement,
        he came to Greece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'There he spent three months, and when a plot was made against him
        by the Jews[[COMMENT(0)]] as he was about to set sail for Syria, he decided
        to return through Macedonia. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: Greek probably refers here to Jewish religious leaders, and others
          under their influence, in that time; also verse 19
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Sopater the Berean, son of Pyrrhus, accompanied him; and of the Thessalonians,
        Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy; and the Asians,
        Tychicus and Trophimus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'These went on ahead and were waiting for us at Troas, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Eutychus Raised from the Dead'
      title: Eutychus Raised from the Dead
      number: 6
      content: 'but we sailed away from Philippi after the days of Unleavened Bread,
        and in five days we came to them at Troas, where we stayed for seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  On the first day of the week, when we were gathered together to
        break bread, Paul talked with them, intending to depart on the next day,
        and he prolonged his speech until midnight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'There were many lamps in the upper room where we were gathered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And a young man named Eutychus, sitting at the window, sank into
        a deep sleep as Paul talked still longer. And being overcome by sleep, he
        fell down from the third story and was taken up dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Paul went down and bent over him, and taking him in his arms,
        said, \u201CDo not be alarmed, for his life is in him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And when Paul had gone up and had broken bread and eaten, he conversed
        with them a long while, until daybreak, and so departed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they took the youth away alive, and were not a little comforted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But going ahead to the ship, we set sail for Assos, intending to
        take Paul aboard there, for so he had arranged, intending himself to go by
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when he met us at Assos, we took him on board and went to Mitylene. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And sailing from there we came the following day opposite Chios;
        the next day we touched at Samos; and[[COMMENT(0)]] the day after that we
        went to Miletus. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:15 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add '
    - name: '16: Paul Speaks to the Ephesian Elders'
      title: Paul Speaks to the Ephesian Elders
      number: 16
      content: 'For Paul had decided to sail past Ephesus, so that he might not have
        to spend time in Asia, for he was hastening to be at Jerusalem, if possible,
        on the day of Pentecost.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now from Miletus he sent to Ephesus and called the elders of the
        church to come to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when they came to him, he said to them:  \u201CYou yourselves
        know how I lived among you the whole time from the first day that I set foot
        in Asia, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'serving the Lord with all humility and with tears and with trials
        that happened to me through the plots of the Jews; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'how I did not shrink from declaring to you anything that was profitable,
        and teaching you in public and from house to house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'testifying both to Jews and to Greeks of repentance toward God and
        of faith in our Lord Jesus Christ.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:21 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts omit '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And now, behold, I am going to Jerusalem, constrained by[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the Spirit, not knowing what will happen to me there, '
      comments:
      - number: '20:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'except that the Holy Spirit testifies to me in every city that imprisonment
        and afflictions await me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But I do not account my life of any value nor as precious to myself,
        if only I may finish my course and the ministry that I received from the
        Lord Jesus, to testify to the gospel of the grace of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And now, behold, I know that none of you among whom I have gone about
        proclaiming the kingdom will see my face again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore I testify to you this day that I am innocent of the blood
        of all, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'for I did not shrink from declaring to you the whole counsel of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Pay careful attention to yourselves and to all the flock, in which
        the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to care for the church of God,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        which he obtained with his own blood.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:28 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts Or '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I know that after my departure fierce wolves will come in among you,
        not sparing the flock; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and from among your own selves will arise men speaking twisted things,
        to draw away the disciples after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore be alert, remembering that for three years I did not cease
        night or day to admonish every one with tears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And now I commend you to God and to the word of his grace, which
        is able to build you up and to give you the inheritance among all those who
        are sanctified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I coveted no one\u2019s silver or gold or apparel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You yourselves know that these hands ministered to my necessities
        and to those who were with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "In all things I have shown you that by working hard in this way we
        must help the weak and remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he himself
        said, <JESUS>\u2018It is more blessed </JESUS><JESUS>to give than to receive.\u2019</JESUS>\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And when he had said these things, he knelt down and prayed with
        them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And there was much weeping on the part of all; they embraced Paul
        and kissed him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: being sorrowful most of all because of the word he had spoken, that
        they would not see his face again. And they accompanied him to the ship.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Goes to Jerusalem'
      title: Paul Goes to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  And when we had parted from them and set sail, we came by a straight
        course to Cos, and the next day to Rhodes, and from there to Patara.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:1 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And having found a ship crossing to Phoenicia, we went aboard and
        set sail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When we had come in sight of Cyprus, leaving it on the left we sailed
        to Syria and landed at Tyre, for there the ship was to unload its cargo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And having sought out the disciples, we stayed there for seven days.
        And through the Spirit they were telling Paul not to go on to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When our days there were ended, we departed and went on our journey,
        and they all, with wives and children, accompanied us until we were outside
        the city. And kneeling down on the beach, we prayed '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and said farewell to one another. Then we went on board the ship,
        and they returned home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When we had finished the voyage from Tyre, we arrived at Ptolemais,
        and we greeted the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] and stayed with them for one day. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:7 '
        content: Or ; also verse 17
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'On the next day we departed and came to Caesarea, and we entered
        the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven, and stayed
        with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He had four unmarried daughters, who prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'While we were staying for many days, a prophet named Agabus came
        down from Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And coming to us, he took Paul\u2019s belt and bound his own feet
        and hands and said, \u201CThus says the Holy Spirit, \u2018This is how the
        Jews[[COMMENT(0)]] at Jerusalem will bind the man who owns this belt and
        deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '21:11 '
        content: Greek probably refers here to Jewish religious leaders, and others
          under their influence, in that time
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When we heard this, we and the people there urged him not to go up
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Paul answered, \u201CWhat are you doing, weeping and breaking
        my heart? For I am ready not only to be imprisoned but even to die in Jerusalem
        for the name of the Lord Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And since he would not be persuaded, we ceased and said, \u201CLet
        the will of the Lord be done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'After these days we got ready and went up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Paul Visits James'
      title: Paul Visits James
      number: 16
      content: 'And some of the disciples from Caesarea went with us, bringing us
        to the house of Mnason of Cyprus, an early disciple, with whom we should
        lodge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When we had come to Jerusalem, the brothers received us gladly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'On the following day Paul went in with us to James, and all the elders
        were present. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After greeting them, he related one by one the things that God had
        done among the Gentiles through his ministry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when they heard it, they glorified God. And they said to him,
        \u201CYou see, brother, how many thousands there are among the Jews of those
        who have believed. They are all zealous for the law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and they have been told about you that you teach all the Jews who
        are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, telling them not to circumcise their
        children or walk according to our customs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'What then is to be done? They will certainly hear that you have come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Do therefore what we tell you. We have four men who are under a vow; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'take these men and purify yourself along with them and pay their
        expenses, so that they may shave their heads. Thus all will know that there
        is nothing in what they have been told about you, but that you yourself also
        live in observance of the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But as for the Gentiles who have believed, we have sent a letter
        with our judgment that they should abstain from what has been sacrificed
        to idols, and from blood, and from what has been strangled,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and from sexual immorality.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '21:25 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts omit '
    - name: '26: Paul Arrested in the Temple'
      title: Paul Arrested in the Temple
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Paul took the men, and the next day he purified himself along
        with them and went into the temple, giving notice when the days of purification
        would be fulfilled and the offering presented for each one of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the seven days were almost completed, the Jews from Asia, seeing
        him in the temple, stirred up the whole crowd and laid hands on him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "crying out, \u201CMen of Israel, help! This is the man who is teaching
        everyone everywhere against the people and the law and this place. Moreover,
        he even brought Greeks into the temple and has defiled this holy place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For they had previously seen Trophimus the Ephesian with him in the
        city, and they supposed that Paul had brought him into the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then all the city was stirred up, and the people ran together. They
        seized Paul and dragged him out of the temple, and at once the gates were
        shut. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And as they were seeking to kill him, word came to the tribune of
        the cohort that all Jerusalem was in confusion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He at once took soldiers and centurions and ran down to them. And
        when they saw the tribune and the soldiers, they stopped beating Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the tribune came up and arrested him and ordered him to be bound
        with two chains. He inquired who he was and what he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Some in the crowd were shouting one thing, some another. And as he
        could not learn the facts because of the uproar, he ordered him to be brought
        into the barracks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And when he came to the steps, he was actually carried by the soldiers
        because of the violence of the crowd, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Paul Speaks to the People'
      title: Paul Speaks to the People
      number: 36
      content: "for the mob of the people followed, crying out, \u201CAway with him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "As Paul was about to be brought into the barracks, he said to the
        tribune, \u201CMay I say something to you?\u201D And he said, \u201CDo you
        know Greek? "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Are you not the Egyptian, then, who recently stirred up a revolt
        and led the four thousand men of the Assassins out into the wilderness?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Paul replied, \u201CI am a Jew, from Tarsus in Cilicia, a citizen
        of no obscure city. I beg you, permit me to speak to the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And when he had given him permission, Paul, standing on the steps,
        motioned with his hand to the people. And when there was a great hush, he
        addressed them in the Hebrew language,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying:'
      comments:
      - number: '21:40 '
        content: Or (probably Aramaic)
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CBrothers and fathers, hear the defense that I now make
        before you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when they heard that he was addressing them in the Hebrew language,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        they became even more quiet. And he said:  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:2 '
        content: Or (probably Aramaic)
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CI am a Jew, born in Tarsus in Cilicia, but brought up in
        this city, educated at the feet of Gamaliel[[COMMENT(0)]]  according to the
        strict manner of the law of our fathers, being zealous for God as all of
        you are this day. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I persecuted this Way to the death, binding and delivering to prison
        both men and women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'as the high priest and the whole council of elders can bear me witness.
        From them I received letters to the brothers, and I journeyed toward Damascus
        to take those also who were there and bring them in bonds to Jerusalem to
        be punished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CAs I was on my way and drew near to Damascus, about noon
        a great light from heaven suddenly shone around me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Saul,
        Saul, why are you persecuting me?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I answered, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 And he said to me,
        <JESUS>\u2018I am </JESUS><JESUS>Jesus of Nazareth, whom you are persecuting.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now those who were with me saw the light but did not understand[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the voice of the one who was speaking to me. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I said, \u2018What shall I do, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said
        to me, <JESUS>\u2018Rise, and go into Damascus, and there you will be told
        all that is appointed for you to do.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And since I could not see because of the brightness of that light,
        I was led by the hand by those who were with me, and came into Damascus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd one Ananias, a devout man according to the law, well spoken
        of by all the Jews who lived there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "came to me, and standing by me said to me, \u2018Brother Saul, receive
        your sight.\u2019 And at that very hour I received my sight and saw him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u2018The God of our fathers appointed you to know his
        will, to see the Righteous One and to hear a voice from his mouth; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for you will be a witness for him to everyone of what you have seen
        and heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And now why do you wait? Rise and be baptized and wash away your
        sins, calling on his name.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CWhen I had returned to Jerusalem and was praying in the temple,
        I fell into a trance "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and saw him saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Make haste and get out of
        Jerusalem quickly, because they will not accept your testimony about me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And I said, \u2018Lord, they themselves know that in one synagogue
        after another I imprisoned and beat those who believed in you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when the blood of Stephen your witness was being shed, I myself
        was standing by and approving and watching over the garments of those who
        killed him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Paul and the Roman Tribune'
      title: Paul and the Roman Tribune
      number: 21
      content: "And he said to me, <JESUS>\u2018Go, for I will send you </JESUS><JESUS>far
        away to the Gentiles.\u2019</JESUS>\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Up to this word they listened to him. Then they raised their voices
        and said, \u201CAway with such a fellow from the earth! For he should not
        be allowed to live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And as they were shouting and throwing off their cloaks and flinging
        dust into the air, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the tribune ordered him to be brought into the barracks, saying that
        he should be examined by flogging, to find out why they were shouting against
        him like this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But when they had stretched him out for the whips,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Paul said to the centurion who was standing by, \u201CIs it lawful for you
        to flog a man who is a Roman citizen and uncondemned?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '22:25 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the centurion heard this, he went to the tribune and said to
        him, \u201CWhat are you about to do? For this man is a Roman citizen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So the tribune came and said to him, \u201CTell me, are you a Roman
        citizen?\u201D And he said, \u201CYes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The tribune answered, \u201CI bought this citizenship for a large
        sum.\u201D Paul said, \u201CBut I am a citizen by birth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Paul Before the Council'
      title: Paul Before the Council
      number: 29
      content: 'So those who were about to examine him withdrew from him immediately,
        and the tribune also was afraid, for he realized that Paul was a Roman citizen
        and that he had bound him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But on the next day, desiring to know the real reason why he was being
        accused by the Jews, he unbound him and commanded the chief priests and all
        the council to meet, and he brought Paul down and set him before them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  And looking intently at the council, Paul said, \u201CBrothers,
        I have lived my life before God in all good conscience up to this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the high priest Ananias commanded those who stood by him to strike
        him on the mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Paul said to him, \u201CGod is going to strike you, you whitewashed
        wall! Are you sitting to judge me according to the law, and yet contrary
        to the law you order me to be struck?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Those who stood by said, \u201CWould you revile God\u2019s high priest?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Paul said, \u201CI did not know, brothers, that he was the high
        priest, for it is written, \u2018You shall not speak evil of a ruler of your
        people.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now when Paul perceived that one part were Sadducees and the other
        Pharisees, he cried out in the council, \u201CBrothers, I am a Pharisee,
        a son of Pharisees. It is with respect to the hope and the resurrection of
        the dead that I am on trial.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when he had said this, a dissension arose between the Pharisees
        and the Sadducees, and the assembly was divided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the Sadducees say that there is no resurrection, nor angel, nor
        spirit, but the Pharisees acknowledge them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then a great clamor arose, and some of the scribes of the Pharisees\u2019
        party stood up and contended sharply, \u201CWe find nothing wrong in this
        man. What if a spirit or an angel spoke to him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when the dissension became violent, the tribune, afraid that
        Paul would be torn to pieces by them, commanded the soldiers to go down and
        take him away from among them by force and bring him into the barracks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Plot to Kill Paul'
      title: A Plot to Kill Paul
      number: 11
      content: "  The following night the Lord stood by him and said, <JESUS>\u201CTake
        courage, for </JESUS><JESUS>as you have testified to the facts about me in
        Jerusalem, so you must </JESUS><JESUS>testify also in Rome.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When it was day, the Jews made a plot and bound themselves by an
        oath neither to eat nor drink till they had killed Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There were more than forty who made this conspiracy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They went to the chief priests and elders and said, \u201CWe have
        strictly bound ourselves by an oath to taste no food till we have killed
        Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now therefore you, along with the council, give notice to the tribune
        to bring him down to you, as though you were going to determine his case
        more exactly. And we are ready to kill him before he comes near.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the son of Paul\u2019s sister heard of their ambush, so he went
        and entered the barracks and told Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Paul called one of the centurions and said, \u201CTake this young
        man to the tribune, for he has something to tell him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he took him and brought him to the tribune and said, \u201CPaul
        the prisoner called me and asked me to bring this young man to you, as he
        has something to say to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The tribune took him by the hand, and going aside asked him privately,
        \u201CWhat is it that you have to tell me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said, \u201CThe Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul
        down to the council tomorrow, as though they were going to inquire somewhat
        more closely about him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But do not be persuaded by them, for more than forty of their men
        are lying in ambush for him, who have bound themselves by an oath neither
        to eat nor drink till they have killed him. And now they are ready, waiting
        for your consent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Paul Sent to Felix the Governor'
      title: Paul Sent to Felix the Governor
      number: 22
      content: "So the tribune dismissed the young man, charging him, \u201CTell
        no one that you have informed me of these things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he called two of the centurions and said, \u201CGet ready two
        hundred soldiers, with seventy horsemen and two hundred spearmen to go as
        far as Caesarea at the third hour of the night.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:23 '
        content: 'That is, 9 '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Also provide mounts for Paul to ride and bring him safely to Felix
        the governor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And he wrote a letter to this effect:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CClaudius Lysias, to his Excellency the governor Felix, greetings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This man was seized by the Jews and was about to be killed by them
        when I came upon them with the soldiers and rescued him, having learned that
        he was a Roman citizen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And desiring to know the charge for which they were accusing him,
        I brought him down to their council. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I found that he was being accused about questions of their law, but
        charged with nothing deserving death or imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And when it was disclosed to me that there would be a plot against
        the man, I sent him to you at once, ordering his accusers also to state before
        you what they have against him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the soldiers, according to their instructions, took Paul and brought
        him by night to Antipatris. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And on the next day they returned to the barracks, letting the horsemen
        go on with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When they had come to Caesarea and delivered the letter to the governor,
        they presented Paul also before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'On reading the letter, he asked what province he was from. And when
        he learned that he was from Cilicia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "he said, \u201CI will give you a hearing when your accusers arrive.\u201D
        And he commanded him to be guarded in Herod\u2019s praetorium."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Before Felix at Caesarea'
      title: Paul Before Felix at Caesarea
      number: 1
      content: '  And after five days the high priest Ananias came down with some
        elders and a spokesman, one Tertullus. They laid before the governor their
        case against Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when he had been summoned, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying:\u201CSince
        through you we enjoy much peace, and since by your foresight, most excellent
        Felix, reforms are being made for this nation, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'in every way and everywhere we accept this with all gratitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But, to detain[[COMMENT(0)]] you no further, I beg you in your kindness
        to hear us briefly. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For we have found this man a plague, one who stirs up riots among
        all the Jews throughout the world and is a ringleader of the sect of the
        Nazarenes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He even tried to profane the temple, but we seized him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:6 '
        content: Some manuscripts add .
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "By examining him yourself you will be able to find out from him about
        everything of which we accuse him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Jews also joined in the charge, affirming that all these things
        were so.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And when the governor had nodded to him to speak, Paul replied:\u201CKnowing
        that for many years you have been a judge over this nation, I cheerfully
        make my defense. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You can verify that it is not more than twelve days since I went
        up to worship in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they did not find me disputing with anyone or stirring up a crowd,
        either in the temple or in the synagogues or in the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Neither can they prove to you what they now bring up against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But this I confess to you, that according to the Way, which they
        call a sect, I worship the God of our fathers, believing everything laid
        down by the Law and written in the Prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'having a hope in God, which these men themselves accept, that there
        will be a resurrection of both the just and the unjust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So I always take pains to have a clear conscience toward both God
        and man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now after several years I came to bring alms to my nation and to
        present offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "While I was doing this, they found me purified in the temple, without
        any crowd or tumult. But some Jews from Asia\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'they ought to be here before you and to make an accusation, should
        they have anything against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Or else let these men themselves say what wrongdoing they found when
        I stood before the council, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Paul Kept in Custody'
      title: Paul Kept in Custody
      number: 21
      content: "other than this one thing that I cried out while standing among them:
        \u2018It is with respect to the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial
        before you this day.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Felix, having a rather accurate knowledge of the Way, put them
        off, saying, \u201CWhen Lysias the tribune comes down, I will decide your
        case.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he gave orders to the centurion that he should be kept in custody
        but have some liberty, and that none of his friends should be prevented from
        attending to his needs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After some days Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who was Jewish,
        and he sent for Paul and heard him speak about faith in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And as he reasoned about righteousness and self-control and the coming
        judgment, Felix was alarmed and said, \u201CGo away for the present. When
        I get an opportunity I will summon you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'At the same time he hoped that money would be given him by Paul.
        So he sent for him often and conversed with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: When two years had elapsed, Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus.
        And desiring to do the Jews a favor, Felix left Paul in prison.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Appeals to Caesar'
      title: Paul Appeals to Caesar
      number: 1
      content: '  Now three days after Festus had arrived in the province, he went
        up to Jerusalem from Caesarea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the chief priests and the principal men of the Jews laid out
        their case against Paul, and they urged him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "asking as a favor against Paul[[COMMENT(0)]] that he summon him to
        Jerusalem\u2014because they were planning an ambush to kill him on the way. "
      comments:
      - number: '25:3 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Festus replied that Paul was being kept at Caesarea and that he himself
        intended to go there shortly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSo,\u201D said he, \u201Clet the men of authority among you
        go down with me, and if there is anything wrong about the man, let them bring
        charges against him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'After he stayed among them not more than eight or ten days, he went
        down to Caesarea. And the next day he took his seat on the tribunal and ordered
        Paul to be brought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When he had arrived, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood
        around him, bringing many and serious charges against him that they could
        not prove. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Paul argued in his defense, \u201CNeither against the law of the
        Jews, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar have I committed any offense.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Festus, wishing to do the Jews a favor, said to Paul, \u201CDo
        you wish to go up to Jerusalem and there be tried on these charges before
        me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Paul said, \u201CI am standing before Caesar\u2019s tribunal,
        where I ought to be tried. To the Jews I have done no wrong, as you yourself
        know very well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If then I am a wrongdoer and have committed anything for which I
        deserve to die, I do not seek to escape death. But if there is nothing to
        their charges against me, no one can give me up to them. I appeal to Caesar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Paul Before Agrippa and Bernice'
      title: Paul Before Agrippa and Bernice
      number: 12
      content: "Then Festus, when he had conferred with his council, answered, \u201CTo
        Caesar you have appealed; to Caesar you shall go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when some days had passed, Agrippa the king and Bernice arrived
        at Caesarea and greeted Festus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And as they stayed there many days, Festus laid Paul\u2019s case
        before the king, saying, \u201CThere is a man left prisoner by Felix, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and when I was at Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of
        the Jews laid out their case against him, asking for a sentence of condemnation
        against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I answered them that it was not the custom of the Romans to give
        up anyone before the accused met the accusers face to face and had opportunity
        to make his defense concerning the charge laid against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So when they came together here, I made no delay, but on the next
        day took my seat on the tribunal and ordered the man to be brought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the accusers stood up, they brought no charge in his case of
        such evils as I supposed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Rather they had certain points of dispute with him about their own
        religion and about a certain Jesus, who was dead, but whom Paul asserted
        to be alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Being at a loss how to investigate these questions, I asked whether
        he wanted to go to Jerusalem and be tried there regarding them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Paul had appealed to be kept in custody for the decision
        of the emperor, I ordered him to be held until I could send him to Caesar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CI would like to hear the man myself.\u201D
        \u201CTomorrow,\u201D said he, \u201Cyou will hear him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So on the next day Agrippa and Bernice came with great pomp, and
        they entered the audience hall with the military tribunes and the prominent
        men of the city. Then, at the command of Festus, Paul was brought in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Festus said, \u201CKing Agrippa and all who are present with
        us, you see this man about whom the whole Jewish people petitioned me, both
        in Jerusalem and here, shouting that he ought not to live any longer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But I found that he had done nothing deserving death. And as he himself
        appealed to the emperor, I decided to go ahead and send him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But I have nothing definite to write to my lord about him. Therefore
        I have brought him before you all, and especially before you, King Agrippa,
        so that, after we have examined him, I may have something to write. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For it seems to me unreasonable, in sending a prisoner, not to indicate
        the charges against him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Defense Before Agrippa"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Defense Before Agrippa"
      number: 1
      content: "  So Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CYou have permission to speak for
        yourself.\u201D Then Paul stretched out his hand and made his defense:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI consider myself fortunate that it is before you, King Agrippa,
        I am going to make my defense today against all the accusations of the Jews, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'especially because you are familiar with all the customs and controversies
        of the Jews. Therefore I beg you to listen to me patiently.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CMy manner of life from my youth, spent from the beginning
        among my own nation and in Jerusalem, is known by all the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have known for a long time, if they are willing to testify,
        that according to the strictest party of our religion I have lived as a Pharisee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now I stand here on trial because of my hope in the promise made
        by God to our fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'to which our twelve tribes hope to attain, as they earnestly worship
        night and day. And for this hope I am accused by Jews, O king! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Why is it thought incredible by any of you that God raises the dead?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CI myself was convinced that I ought to do many things in
        opposing the name of Jesus of Nazareth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I did so in Jerusalem. I not only locked up many of the saints
        in prison after receiving authority from the chief priests, but when they
        were put to death I cast my vote against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Paul Tells of His Conversion'
      title: Paul Tells of His Conversion
      number: 11
      content: 'And I punished them often in all the synagogues and tried to make
        them blaspheme, and in raging fury against them I persecuted them even to
        foreign cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIn this connection I journeyed to Damascus with the authority
        and commission of the chief priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'At midday, O king, I saw on the way a light from heaven, brighter
        than the sun, that shone around me and those who journeyed with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when we had all fallen to the ground, I heard a voice saying
        to me in the Hebrew language,[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u2018Saul, Saul, why
        are you persecuting me? It is hard for you to kick against the goads.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:14 '
        content: Or (probably Aramaic)
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I said, \u2018Who are you, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said, <JESUS>\u2018I
        am Jesus whom you are persecuting.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>But rise and </JESUS><JESUS>stand upon your feet, for I have
        appeared to you for this purpose, </JESUS><JESUS>to appoint you as a servant
        and witness to the things in which you have seen me and to those in which
        I will appear to you,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>delivering you from your people and from the Gentiles\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>to
        whom I </JESUS><JESUS>am sending you</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>to open their eyes, so that they may turn from darkness to
        light and from </JESUS><JESUS>the power of Satan to God, that they may receive
        </JESUS><JESUS>forgiveness of sins and </JESUS><JESUS>a place among those
        who are sanctified </JESUS><JESUS>by faith in me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CTherefore, O King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly
        vision, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but declared first to those in Damascus, then in Jerusalem and throughout
        all the region of Judea, and also to the Gentiles, that they should repent
        and turn to God, performing deeds in keeping with their repentance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For this reason the Jews seized me in the temple and tried to kill
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'To this day I have had the help that comes from God, and so I stand
        here testifying both to small and great, saying nothing but what the prophets
        and Moses said would come to pass: '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that the Christ must suffer and that, by being the first to rise
        from the dead, he would proclaim light both to our people and to the Gentiles.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And as he was saying these things in his defense, Festus said with
        a loud voice, \u201CPaul, you are out of your mind; your great learning is
        driving you out of your mind.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Paul said, \u201CI am not out of my mind, most excellent Festus,
        but I am speaking true and rational words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the king knows about these things, and to him I speak boldly.
        For I am persuaded that none of these things has escaped his notice, for
        this has not been done in a corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you believe.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CIn a short time would you persuade
        me to be a Christian?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:28 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Paul said, \u201CWhether short or long, I would to God that not
        only you but also all who hear me this day might become such as I am\u2014except
        for these chains.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the king rose, and the governor and Bernice and those who were
        sitting with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And when they had withdrawn, they said to one another, \u201CThis
        man is doing nothing to deserve death or imprisonment.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CThis man could have been set free
        if he had not appealed to Caesar.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Sails for Rome'
      title: Paul Sails for Rome
      number: 1
      content: '  And when it was decided that we should sail for Italy, they delivered
        Paul and some other prisoners to a centurion of the Augustan Cohort named
        Julius. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And embarking in a ship of Adramyttium, which was about to sail to
        the ports along the coast of Asia, we put to sea, accompanied by Aristarchus,
        a Macedonian from Thessalonica. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The next day we put in at Sidon. And Julius treated Paul kindly and
        gave him leave to go to his friends and be cared for. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And putting out to sea from there we sailed under the lee of Cyprus,
        because the winds were against us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when we had sailed across the open sea along the coast of Cilicia
        and Pamphylia, we came to Myra in Lycia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing for Italy
        and put us on board. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We sailed slowly for a number of days and arrived with difficulty
        off Cnidus, and as the wind did not allow us to go farther, we sailed under
        the lee of Crete off Salmone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Coasting along it with difficulty, we came to a place called Fair
        Havens, near which was the city of Lasea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Since much time had passed, and the voyage was now dangerous because
        even the Fast[[COMMENT(0)]] was already over, Paul advised them, '
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        content: That is, the Day of Atonement
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "saying, \u201CSirs, I perceive that the voyage will be with injury
        and much loss, not only of the cargo and the ship, but also of our lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the centurion paid more attention to the pilot and to the owner
        of the ship than to what Paul said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Storm at Sea'
      title: The Storm at Sea
      number: 12
      content: 'And because the harbor was not suitable to spend the winter in, the
        majority decided to put out to sea from there, on the chance that somehow
        they could reach Phoenix, a harbor of Crete, facing both southwest and northwest,
        and spend the winter there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when the south wind blew gently, supposing that they had obtained
        their purpose, they weighed anchor and sailed along Crete, close to the shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But soon a tempestuous wind, called the northeaster, struck down
        from the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when the ship was caught and could not face the wind, we gave
        way to it and were driven along. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Running under the lee of a small island called Cauda,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        we managed with difficulty to secure the ship\u2019s boat. "
      comments:
      - number: '27:16 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After hoisting it up, they used supports to undergird the ship. Then,
        fearing that they would run aground on the Syrtis, they lowered the gear,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and thus they were driven along. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:17 '
        content: That is, the sea-anchor (or possibly the mainsail)
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Since we were violently storm-tossed, they began the next day to
        jettison the cargo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And on the third day they threw the ship\u2019s tackle overboard
        with their own hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When neither sun nor stars appeared for many days, and no small tempest
        lay on us, all hope of our being saved was at last abandoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Since they had been without food for a long time, Paul stood up among
        them and said, \u201CMen, you should have listened to me and not have set
        sail from Crete and incurred this injury and loss. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Yet now I urge you to take heart, for there will be no loss of life
        among you, but only of the ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For this very night there stood before me an angel of the God to
        whom I belong and whom I worship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and he said, \u2018Do not be afraid, Paul; you must stand before
        Caesar. And behold, God has granted you all those who sail with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So take heart, men, for I have faith in God that it will be exactly
        as I have been told. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But we must run aground on some island.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the fourteenth night had come, as we were being driven across
        the Adriatic Sea, about midnight the sailors suspected that they were nearing
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So they took a sounding and found twenty fathoms.[[COMMENT(0)]] A
        little farther on they took a sounding again and found fifteen fathoms.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:28 '
        content: About 120 feet; a fathom (Greek ) was about 6 feet or 2 metersAbout
          90 feet (see previous note)
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And fearing that we might run on the rocks, they let down four anchors
        from the stern and prayed for day to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And as the sailors were seeking to escape from the ship, and had
        lowered the ship\u2019s boat into the sea under pretense of laying out anchors
        from the bow, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, \u201CUnless these men
        stay in the ship, you cannot be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then the soldiers cut away the ropes of the ship\u2019s boat and
        let it go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "As day was about to dawn, Paul urged them all to take some food,
        saying, \u201CToday is the fourteenth day that you have continued in suspense
        and without food, having taken nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Therefore I urge you to take some food. For it will give you strength,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for not a hair is to perish from the head of any of you.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '27:34 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And when he had said these things, he took bread, and giving thanks
        to God in the presence of all he broke it and began to eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then they all were encouraged and ate some food themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '(We were in all 276[[COMMENT(0)]]  persons in the ship.) '
      comments:
      - number: '27:37 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts , or '
    - name: '38: The Shipwreck'
      title: The Shipwreck
      number: 38
      content: 'And when they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship, throwing
        out the wheat into the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now when it was day, they did not recognize the land, but they noticed
        a bay with a beach, on which they planned if possible to run the ship ashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So they cast off the anchors and left them in the sea, at the same
        time loosening the ropes that tied the rudders. Then hoisting the foresail
        to the wind they made for the beach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'But striking a reef,[[COMMENT(0)]]  they ran the vessel aground.
        The bow stuck and remained immovable, and the stern was being broken up by
        the surf. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:41 '
        content: 'Or , or ; Greek '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "The soldiers\u2019 plan was to kill the prisoners, lest any should
        swim away and escape. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'But the centurion, wishing to save Paul, kept them from carrying
        out their plan. He ordered those who could swim to jump overboard first and
        make for the land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: and the rest on planks or on pieces of the ship. And so it was that
        all were brought safely to land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul on Malta'
      title: Paul on Malta
      number: 1
      content: '  After we were brought safely through, we then learned that the
        island was called Malta. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The native people[[COMMENT(0)]] showed us unusual kindness, for they
        kindled a fire and welcomed us all, because it had begun to rain and was
        cold. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:2 '
        content: "Greek (that is, non\u2013Greek speakers); also verse 4"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks and put them on the fire,
        a viper came out because of the heat and fastened on his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the native people saw the creature hanging from his hand, they
        said to one another, \u201CNo doubt this man is a murderer. Though he has
        escaped from the sea, Justice[[COMMENT(0)]] has not allowed him to live.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '28:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He, however, shook off the creature into the fire and suffered no
        harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They were waiting for him to swell up or suddenly fall down dead.
        But when they had waited a long time and saw no misfortune come to him, they
        changed their minds and said that he was a god.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now in the neighborhood of that place were lands belonging to the
        chief man of the island, named Publius, who received us and entertained us
        hospitably for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It happened that the father of Publius lay sick with fever and dysentery.
        And Paul visited him and prayed, and putting his hands on him, healed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when this had taken place, the rest of the people on the island
        who had diseases also came and were cured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Paul Arrives at Rome'
      title: Paul Arrives at Rome
      number: 10
      content: 'They also honored us greatly,[[COMMENT(0)]] and when we were about
        to sail, they put on board whatever we needed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:10 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After three months we set sail in a ship that had wintered in the
        island, a ship of Alexandria, with the twin gods[[COMMENT(0)]] as a figurehead. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:11 '
        content: That is, the Greek gods Castor and Pollux
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Putting in at Syracuse, we stayed there for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And from there we made a circuit and arrived at Rhegium. And after
        one day a south wind sprang up, and on the second day we came to Puteoli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There we found brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] and were invited to stay with
        them for seven days. And so we came to Rome. '
      comments:
      - number: '28:14 '
        content: Or ; also verses 15, 21
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the brothers there, when they heard about us, came as far as
        the Forum of Appius and Three Taverns to meet us. On seeing them, Paul thanked
        God and took courage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Paul in Rome'
      title: Paul in Rome
      number: 16
      content: 'And when we came into Rome, Paul was allowed to stay by himself,
        with the soldier who guarded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "After three days he called together the local leaders of the Jews,
        and when they had gathered, he said to them, \u201CBrothers, though I had
        done nothing against our people or the customs of our fathers, yet I was
        delivered as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When they had examined me, they wished to set me at liberty, because
        there was no reason for the death penalty in my case. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But because the Jews objected, I was compelled to appeal to Caesar\u2014though
        I had no charge to bring against my nation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For this reason, therefore, I have asked to see you and speak with
        you, since it is because of the hope of Israel that I am wearing this chain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWe have received no letters from Judea
        about you, and none of the brothers coming here has reported or spoken any
        evil about you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But we desire to hear from you what your views are, for with regard
        to this sect we know that everywhere it is spoken against.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When they had appointed a day for him, they came to him at his lodging
        in greater numbers. From morning till evening he expounded to them, testifying
        to the kingdom of God and trying to convince them about Jesus both from the
        Law of Moses and from the Prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And some were convinced by what he said, but others disbelieved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And disagreeing among themselves, they departed after Paul had made
        one statement: \u201CThe Holy Spirit was right in saying to your fathers
        through Isaiah the prophet:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Go to this people, and say,  \u201CYou will indeed
        hear but never understand,and you will indeed see but never perceive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  For this people\u2019s heart has grown dull,and with their ears
        they can barely hear,and their eyes they have closed;lest they should see
        with their eyesand hear with their earsand understand with their heartand
        turn, and I would heal them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
